var book = {
	"name": "John",
	"numChapters": 21,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In the beginning was the Word,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26046A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26046A\"></sup> and the Word was with God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26046B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26046B\"></sup> and the Word was God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26046C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26046C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He was with God in the beginning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26047D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26047D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Through him all things were made; without him nothing was made that has been made.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26048E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26048E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>In him was life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26049F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26049F\"></sup> and that life was the light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26049G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26049G\"></sup> of all mankind.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The light shines in the darkness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26050H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26050H\"></sup> and the darkness has not overcome it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26050I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26050I\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>There was a man sent from God whose name was John.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26051J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26051J\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He came as a witness to testify<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26052K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26052K\"></sup> concerning that light, so that through him all might believe.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26052L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26052L\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He himself was not the light; he came only as a witness to the light.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The true light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26054M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26054M\"></sup> that gives light to everyone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26054N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26054N\"></sup> was coming into the world.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He was in the world, and though the world was made through him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26055O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26055O\"></sup> the world did not recognize him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He came to that which was his own, but his own did not receive him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26056P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26056P\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Yet to all who did receive him, to those who believed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26057Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26057Q\"></sup> in his name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26057R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26057R\"></sup> he gave the right to become children of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26057S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26057S\"></sup>—",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>children born not of natural descent, nor of human decision or a husband’s will, but born of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26058T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26058T\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Word became flesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26059U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26059U\"></sup> and made his dwelling among us. We have seen his glory,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26059V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26059V\"></sup> the glory of the one and only Son, who came from the Father, full of grace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26059W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26059W\"></sup> and truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26059X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26059X\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>(John testified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26060Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26060Y\"></sup> concerning him. He cried out, saying, “This is the one I spoke about when I said, ‘He who comes after me has surpassed me because he was before me.’”)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26060Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26060Z\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Out of his fullness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26061AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26061AA\"></sup> we have all received grace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26061AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26061AB\"></sup> in place of grace already given.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the law was given through Moses;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26062AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26062AC\"></sup> grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26062AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26062AD\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>No one has ever seen God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26063AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26063AE\"></sup> but the one and only Son, who is himself God and<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26063AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26063AF\"></sup> is in closest relationship with the Father, has made him known.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now this was John’s<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26064AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26064AG\"></sup> testimony when the Jewish leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26064AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26064AH\"></sup> in Jerusalem sent priests and Levites to ask him who he was.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He did not fail to confess, but confessed freely, “I am not the Messiah.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26065AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26065AI\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They asked him, “Then who are you? Are you Elijah?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26066AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26066AJ\"></sup>He said, “I am not.”“Are you the Prophet?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26066AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26066AK\"></sup>He answered, “No.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Finally they said, “Who are you? Give us an answer to take back to those who sent us. What do you say about yourself?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>John replied in the words of Isaiah the prophet, “I am the voice of one calling in the wilderness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26068AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26068AL\"></sup> ‘Make straight the way for the Lord.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26068AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26068AM\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now the Pharisees who had been sent",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>questioned him, “Why then do you baptize if you are not the Messiah, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“I baptize with water,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26071AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26071AN\"></sup> John replied, “but among you stands one you do not know.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He is the one who comes after me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26072AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26072AO\"></sup> the straps of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26072AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26072AP\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>This all happened at Bethany on the other side of the Jordan,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26073AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26073AQ\"></sup> where John was baptizing.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The next day John saw Jesus coming toward him and said, “Look, the Lamb of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26074AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26074AR\"></sup> who takes away the sin of the world!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26074AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26074AS\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>This is the one I meant when I said, ‘A man who comes after me has surpassed me because he was before me.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26075AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26075AT\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I myself did not know him, but the reason I came baptizing with water was that he might be revealed to Israel.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then John gave this testimony: “I saw the Spirit come down from heaven as a dove and remain on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26077AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26077AU\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And I myself did not know him, but the one who sent me to baptize with water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26078AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26078AV\"></sup> told me, ‘The man on whom you see the Spirit come down and remain is the one who will baptize with the Holy Spirit.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26078AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26078AW\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>I have seen and I testify that this is God’s Chosen One.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26079AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26079AX\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The next day John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26080AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26080AZ\"></sup> was there again with two of his disciples.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>When he saw Jesus passing by, he said, “Look, the Lamb of God!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26081BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26081BA\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>When the two disciples heard him say this, they followed Jesus.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Turning around, Jesus saw them following and asked, <span class=\"woj\">“What do you want?”</span>They said, “Rabbi”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26083BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26083BB\"></sup> (which means “Teacher”), “where are you staying?”",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“Come,”</span> he replied, <span class=\"woj\">“and you will see.”</span>So they went and saw where he was staying, and they spent that day with him. It was about four in the afternoon.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother, was one of the two who heard what John had said and who had followed Jesus.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The first thing Andrew did was to find his brother Simon and tell him, “We have found the Messiah” (that is, the Christ).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26086BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26086BC\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And he brought him to Jesus.Jesus looked at him and said, <span class=\"woj\">“You are Simon son of John. You will be called<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26087BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26087BD\"></sup> Cephas”</span> (which, when translated, is Peter).<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26087BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26087BE\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The next day Jesus decided to leave for Galilee. Finding Philip,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26088BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26088BF\"></sup> he said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Follow me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26088BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26088BG\"></sup></span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Philip, like Andrew and Peter, was from the town of Bethsaida.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26089BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26089BH\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Philip found Nathanael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26090BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26090BI\"></sup> and told him, “We have found the one Moses wrote about in the Law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26090BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26090BJ\"></sup> and about whom the prophets also wrote<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26090BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26090BK\"></sup>—Jesus of Nazareth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26090BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26090BL\"></sup> the son of Joseph.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26090BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26090BM\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Nazareth! Can anything good come from there?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26091BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26091BN\"></sup> Nathanael asked.“Come and see,” said Philip.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When Jesus saw Nathanael approaching, he said of him, <span class=\"woj\">“Here truly is an Israelite<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26092BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26092BO\"></sup> in whom there is no deceit.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26092BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26092BP\"></sup></span>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“How do you know me?” Nathanael asked.Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“I saw you while you were still under the fig tree before Philip called you.”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Then Nathanael declared, “Rabbi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26094BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26094BQ\"></sup> you are the Son of God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26094BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26094BR\"></sup> you are the king of Israel.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26094BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26094BS\"></sup>",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“You believe because I told you I saw you under the fig tree. You will see greater things than that.”</span>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>He then added, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, you will see ‘heaven open,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26096BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26096BT\"></sup> and the angels of God ascending and descending<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26096BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26096BU\"></sup> on’ the Son of Man.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26096BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26096BV\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>On the third day a wedding took place at Cana in Galilee.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26097A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26097A\"></sup> Jesus’ mother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26097B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26097B\"></sup> was there,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and Jesus and his disciples had also been invited to the wedding.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the wine was gone, Jesus’ mother said to him, “They have no more wine.”",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Woman,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26100C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26100C\"></sup> why do you involve me?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26100D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26100D\"></sup></span> Jesus replied. <span class=\"woj\">“My hour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26100E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26100E\"></sup> has not yet come.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>His mother said to the servants, “Do whatever he tells you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26101F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26101F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Nearby stood six stone water jars, the kind used by the Jews for ceremonial washing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26102G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26102G\"></sup> each holding from twenty to thirty gallons.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jesus said to the servants, <span class=\"woj\">“Fill the jars with water”</span>; so they filled them to the brim.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then he told them, <span class=\"woj\">“Now draw some out and take it to the master of the banquet.”</span>They did so,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and the master of the banquet tasted the water that had been turned into wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26105H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26105H\"></sup> He did not realize where it had come from, though the servants who had drawn the water knew. Then he called the bridegroom aside",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and said, “Everyone brings out the choice wine first and then the cheaper wine after the guests have had too much to drink; but you have saved the best till now.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>What Jesus did here in Cana of Galilee was the first of the signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26107I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26107I\"></sup> through which he revealed his glory;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26107J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26107J\"></sup> and his disciples believed in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26107K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26107K\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>After this he went down to Capernaum<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26108L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26108L\"></sup> with his mother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26108M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26108M\"></sup> and brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26108N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26108N\"></sup> and his disciples. There they stayed for a few days.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When it was almost time for the Jewish Passover,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26109P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26109P\"></sup> Jesus went up to Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26109Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26109Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the temple courts he found people selling cattle, sheep and doves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26110R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26110R\"></sup> and others sitting at tables exchanging money.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26110S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26110S\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So he made a whip out of cords, and drove all from the temple courts, both sheep and cattle; he scattered the coins of the money changers and overturned their tables.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>To those who sold doves he said, <span class=\"woj\">“Get these out of here! Stop turning my Father’s house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26112T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26112T\"></sup> into a market!”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>His disciples remembered that it is written: “Zeal for your house will consume me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26113U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26113U\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26114V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26114V\"></sup> then responded to him, “What sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26114W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26114W\"></sup> can you show us to prove your authority to do all this?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26114X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26114X\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jesus answered them, <span class=\"woj\">“Destroy this temple, and I will raise it again in three days.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26115Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26115Y\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They replied, “It has taken forty-six years to build this temple, and you are going to raise it in three days?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But the temple he had spoken of was his body.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26117Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26117Z\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After he was raised from the dead, his disciples recalled what he had said.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26118AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26118AA\"></sup> Then they believed the scripture<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26118AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26118AB\"></sup> and the words that Jesus had spoken.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now while he was in Jerusalem at the Passover Festival,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26119AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26119AC\"></sup> many people saw the signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26119AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26119AD\"></sup> he was performing and believed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26119AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26119AE\"></sup> in his name.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But Jesus would not entrust himself to them, for he knew all people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He did not need any testimony about mankind,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26121AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26121AF\"></sup> for he knew what was in each person.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26121AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26121AG\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now there was a Pharisee, a man named Nicodemus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26122A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26122A\"></sup> who was a member of the Jewish ruling council.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26122B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26122B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He came to Jesus at night and said, “Rabbi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26123C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26123C\"></sup> we know<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26123D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26123D\"></sup> that you are a teacher who has come from God. For no one could perform the signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26123E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26123E\"></sup> you are doing if God were not with him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26123F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26123F\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, no one can see the kingdom of God unless they are born again.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26124G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26124G\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“How can someone be born when they are old?” Nicodemus asked. “Surely they cannot enter a second time into their mother’s womb to be born!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, no one can enter the kingdom of God unless they are born of water and the Spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26126H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26126H\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Flesh gives birth to flesh, but the Spirit gives birth to spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26127I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26127I\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You should not be surprised at my saying, ‘You must be born again.’</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The wind blows wherever it pleases. You hear its sound, but you cannot tell where it comes from or where it is going. So it is with everyone born of the Spirit.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26129J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26129J\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“How can this be?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26130K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26130K\"></sup> Nicodemus asked.",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“You are Israel’s teacher,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26131L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26131L\"></sup></span> said Jesus, <span class=\"woj\">“and do you not understand these things?</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Very truly I tell you, we speak of what we know,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26132M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26132M\"></sup> and we testify to what we have seen, but still you people do not accept our testimony.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26132N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26132N\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I have spoken to you of earthly things and you do not believe; how then will you believe if I speak of heavenly things?</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>No one has ever gone into heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26134O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26134O\"></sup> except the one who came from heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26134P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26134P\"></sup>—the Son of Man.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26134Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26134Q\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Just as Moses lifted up the snake in the wilderness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26135R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26135R\"></sup> so the Son of Man must be lifted up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26135S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26135S\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>that everyone who believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26136T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26136T\"></sup> may have eternal life in him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26136U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26136U\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For God so loved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26137V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26137V\"></sup> the world that he gave<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26137W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26137W\"></sup> his one and only Son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26137X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26137X\"></sup> that whoever believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26137Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26137Y\"></sup> in him shall not perish but have eternal life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26137Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26137Z\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For God did not send his Son into the world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26138AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26138AA\"></sup> to condemn the world, but to save the world through him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26138AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26138AB\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whoever believes in him is not condemned,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26139AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26139AC\"></sup> but whoever does not believe stands condemned already because they have not believed in the name of God’s one and only Son.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26139AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26139AD\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>This is the verdict: Light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26140AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26140AE\"></sup> has come into the world, but people loved darkness instead of light because their deeds were evil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26140AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26140AF\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Everyone who does evil hates the light, and will not come into the light for fear that their deeds will be exposed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26141AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26141AG\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But whoever lives by the truth comes into the light, so that it may be seen plainly that what they have done has been done in the sight of God.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After this, Jesus and his disciples went out into the Judean countryside, where he spent some time with them, and baptized.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26143AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26143AH\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26144AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26144AI\"></sup> also was baptizing at Aenon near Salim, because there was plenty of water, and people were coming and being baptized.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>(This was before John was put in prison.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26145AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26145AJ\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>An argument developed between some of John’s disciples and a certain Jew over the matter of ceremonial washing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26146AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26146AK\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They came to John and said to him, “Rabbi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26147AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26147AL\"></sup> that man who was with you on the other side of the Jordan—the one you testified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26147AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26147AM\"></sup> about—look, he is baptizing, and everyone is going to him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>To this John replied, “A person can receive only what is given them from heaven.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You yourselves can testify that I said, ‘I am not the Messiah but am sent ahead of him.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26149AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26149AN\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The bride belongs to the bridegroom.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26150AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26150AO\"></sup> The friend who attends the bridegroom waits and listens for him, and is full of joy when he hears the bridegroom’s voice. That joy is mine, and it is now complete.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26150AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26150AP\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He must become greater; I must become less.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The one who comes from above<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26152AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26152AQ\"></sup> is above all; the one who is from the earth belongs to the earth, and speaks as one from the earth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26152AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26152AR\"></sup> The one who comes from heaven is above all.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>He testifies to what he has seen and heard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26153AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26153AS\"></sup> but no one accepts his testimony.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26153AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26153AT\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Whoever has accepted it has certified that God is truthful.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For the one whom God has sent<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26155AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26155AU\"></sup> speaks the words of God, for God gives the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26155AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26155AV\"></sup> without limit.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The Father loves the Son and has placed everything in his hands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26156AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26156AW\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Whoever believes in the Son has eternal life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26157AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26157AX\"></sup> but whoever rejects the Son will not see life, for God’s wrath remains on them."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now Jesus learned that the Pharisees had heard that he was gaining and baptizing more disciples than John<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26158A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26158A\"></sup>—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>although in fact it was not Jesus who baptized, but his disciples.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So he left Judea<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26160B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26160B\"></sup> and went back once more to Galilee.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now he had to go through Samaria.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26161C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26161C\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he came to a town in Samaria called Sychar, near the plot of ground Jacob had given to his son Joseph.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26162D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26162D\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jacob’s well was there, and Jesus, tired as he was from the journey, sat down by the well. It was about noon.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When a Samaritan woman came to draw water, Jesus said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Will you give me a drink?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26164E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26164E\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>(His disciples had gone into the town<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26165F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26165F\"></sup> to buy food.)",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Samaritan woman said to him, “You are a Jew and I am a Samaritan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26166G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26166G\"></sup> woman. How can you ask me for a drink?” (For Jews do not associate with Samaritans.)",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jesus answered her, <span class=\"woj\">“If you knew the gift of God and who it is that asks you for a drink, you would have asked him and he would have given you living water.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26167H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26167H\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Sir,” the woman said, “you have nothing to draw with and the well is deep. Where can you get this living water?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Are you greater than our father Jacob, who gave us the well<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26169I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26169I\"></sup> and drank from it himself, as did also his sons and his livestock?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Everyone who drinks this water will be thirsty again,</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>but whoever drinks the water I give them will never thirst.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26171J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26171J\"></sup> Indeed, the water I give them will become in them a spring of water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26171K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26171K\"></sup> welling up to eternal life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26171L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26171L\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The woman said to him, “Sir, give me this water so that I won’t get thirsty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26172M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26172M\"></sup> and have to keep coming here to draw water.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He told her, <span class=\"woj\">“Go, call your husband and come back.”</span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“I have no husband,” she replied.Jesus said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“You are right when you say you have no husband.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The fact is, you have had five husbands, and the man you now have is not your husband. What you have just said is quite true.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Sir,” the woman said, “I can see that you are a prophet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26176N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26176N\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Our ancestors worshiped on this mountain,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26177O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26177O\"></sup> but you Jews claim that the place where we must worship is in Jerusalem.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26177P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26177P\"></sup>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Woman,”</span> Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“believe me, a time is coming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26178Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26178Q\"></sup> when you will worship the Father neither on this mountain nor in Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26178R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26178R\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You Samaritans worship what you do not know;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26179S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26179S\"></sup> we worship what we do know, for salvation is from the Jews.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26179T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26179T\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Yet a time is coming and has now come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26180U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26180U\"></sup> when the true worshipers will worship the Father in the Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26180V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26180V\"></sup> and in truth, for they are the kind of worshipers the Father seeks.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>God is spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26181W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26181W\"></sup> and his worshipers must worship in the Spirit and in truth.”</span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The woman said, “I know that Messiah” (called Christ)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26182X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26182X\"></sup> “is coming. When he comes, he will explain everything to us.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Jesus declared, <span class=\"woj\">“I, the one speaking to you—I am he.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26183Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26183Y\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Just then his disciples returned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26184Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26184Z\"></sup> and were surprised to find him talking with a woman. But no one asked, “What do you want?” or “Why are you talking with her?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then, leaving her water jar, the woman went back to the town and said to the people,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“Come, see a man who told me everything I ever did.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26186AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26186AA\"></sup> Could this be the Messiah?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26186AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26186AB\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>They came out of the town and made their way toward him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Meanwhile his disciples urged him, “Rabbi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26188AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26188AC\"></sup> eat something.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I have food to eat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26189AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26189AD\"></sup> that you know nothing about.”</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then his disciples said to each other, “Could someone have brought him food?”",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“My food,”</span> said Jesus, <span class=\"woj\">“is to do the will<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26191AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26191AE\"></sup> of him who sent me and to finish his work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26191AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26191AF\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Don’t you have a saying, ‘It’s still four months until harvest’? I tell you, open your eyes and look at the fields! They are ripe for harvest.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26192AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26192AG\"></sup></span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Even now the one who reaps draws a wage and harvests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26193AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26193AH\"></sup> a crop for eternal life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26193AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26193AI\"></sup> so that the sower and the reaper may be glad together.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Thus the saying ‘One sows and another reaps’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26194AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26194AJ\"></sup> is true.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>I sent you to reap what you have not worked for. Others have done the hard work, and you have reaped the benefits of their labor.”</span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Many of the Samaritans from that town<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26196AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26196AK\"></sup> believed in him because of the woman’s testimony, “He told me everything I ever did.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26196AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26196AL\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So when the Samaritans came to him, they urged him to stay with them, and he stayed two days.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And because of his words many more became believers.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They said to the woman, “We no longer believe just because of what you said; now we have heard for ourselves, and we know that this man really is the Savior of the world.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26199AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26199AM\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>After the two days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26200AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26200AN\"></sup> he left for Galilee.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>(Now Jesus himself had pointed out that a prophet has no honor in his own country.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26201AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26201AO\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>When he arrived in Galilee, the Galileans welcomed him. They had seen all that he had done in Jerusalem at the Passover Festival,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26202AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26202AP\"></sup> for they also had been there.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Once more he visited Cana in Galilee, where he had turned the water into wine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26203AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26203AQ\"></sup> And there was a certain royal official whose son lay sick at Capernaum.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>When this man heard that Jesus had arrived in Galilee from Judea,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26204AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26204AR\"></sup> he went to him and begged him to come and heal his son, who was close to death.",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“Unless you people see signs and wonders,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26205AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26205AS\"></sup></span> Jesus told him, <span class=\"woj\">“you will never believe.”</span>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>The royal official said, “Sir, come down before my child dies.”",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>“Go,”</span> Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“your son will live.”</span>The man took Jesus at his word and departed.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>While he was still on the way, his servants met him with the news that his boy was living.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>When he inquired as to the time when his son got better, they said to him, “Yesterday, at one in the afternoon, the fever left him.”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Then the father realized that this was the exact time at which Jesus had said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Your son will live.”</span> So he and his whole household<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26210AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26210AT\"></sup> believed.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>This was the second sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26211AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26211AU\"></sup> Jesus performed after coming from Judea to Galilee."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Some time later, Jesus went up to Jerusalem for one of the Jewish festivals.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now there is in Jerusalem near the Sheep Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26213A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26213A\"></sup> a pool, which in Aramaic<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26213B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26213B\"></sup> is called Bethesda and which is surrounded by five covered colonnades.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Here a great number of disabled people used to lie—the blind, the lame, the paralyzed.<sup class=\"versenum\">[4] </sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>One who was there had been an invalid for thirty-eight years.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Jesus saw him lying there and learned that he had been in this condition for a long time, he asked him, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you want to get well?”</span>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Sir,” the invalid replied, “I have no one to help me into the pool when the water is stirred. While I am trying to get in, someone else goes down ahead of me.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Jesus said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Get up! Pick up your mat and walk.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26219C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26219C\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>At once the man was cured; he picked up his mat and walked.The day on which this took place was a Sabbath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26220D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26220D\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and so the Jewish leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26221E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26221E\"></sup> said to the man who had been healed, “It is the Sabbath; the law forbids you to carry your mat.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26221F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26221F\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But he replied, “The man who made me well said to me, <span class=\"woj\">‘Pick up your mat and walk.’</span> ”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So they asked him, “Who is this fellow who told you to pick it up and walk?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The man who was healed had no idea who it was, for Jesus had slipped away into the crowd that was there.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Later Jesus found him at the temple and said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“See, you are well again. Stop sinning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26225G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26225G\"></sup> or something worse may happen to you.”</span>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The man went away and told the Jewish leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26226H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26226H\"></sup> that it was Jesus who had made him well.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So, because Jesus was doing these things on the Sabbath, the Jewish leaders began to persecute him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In his defense Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“My Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26228I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26228I\"></sup> is always at his work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26228J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26228J\"></sup> to this very day, and I too am working.”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For this reason they tried all the more to kill him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26229K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26229K\"></sup> not only was he breaking the Sabbath, but he was even calling God his own Father, making himself equal with God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26229L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26229L\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jesus gave them this answer: <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, the Son can do nothing by himself;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26230M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26230M\"></sup> he can do only what he sees his Father doing, because whatever the Father does the Son also does.</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For the Father loves the Son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26231N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26231N\"></sup> and shows him all he does. Yes, and he will show him even greater works than these,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26231O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26231O\"></sup> so that you will be amazed.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For just as the Father raises the dead and gives them life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26232P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26232P\"></sup> even so the Son gives life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26232Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26232Q\"></sup> to whom he is pleased to give it.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Moreover, the Father judges no one, but has entrusted all judgment to the Son,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26233R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26233R\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>that all may honor the Son just as they honor the Father. Whoever does not honor the Son does not honor the Father, who sent him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26234S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26234S\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Very truly I tell you, whoever hears my word and believes him who sent me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26235T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26235T\"></sup> has eternal life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26235U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26235U\"></sup> and will not be judged<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26235V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26235V\"></sup> but has crossed over from death to life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26235W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26235W\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Very truly I tell you, a time is coming and has now come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26236X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26236X\"></sup> when the dead will hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26236Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26236Y\"></sup> the voice of the Son of God and those who hear will live.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For as the Father has life in himself, so he has granted the Son also to have life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26237Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26237Z\"></sup> in himself.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And he has given him authority to judge<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26238AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26238AA\"></sup> because he is the Son of Man.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“Do not be amazed at this, for a time is coming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26239AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26239AB\"></sup> when all who are in their graves will hear his voice</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and come out—those who have done what is good will rise to live, and those who have done what is evil will rise to be condemned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26240AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26240AC\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>By myself I can do nothing;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26241AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26241AD\"></sup> I judge only as I hear, and my judgment is just,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26241AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26241AE\"></sup> for I seek not to please myself but him who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26241AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26241AF\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“If I testify about myself, my testimony is not true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26242AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26242AG\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>There is another who testifies in my favor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26243AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26243AH\"></sup> and I know that his testimony about me is true.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“You have sent to John and he has testified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26244AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26244AI\"></sup> to the truth.</span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Not that I accept human testimony;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26245AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26245AJ\"></sup> but I mention it that you may be saved.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26245AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26245AK\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>John was a lamp that burned and gave light,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26246AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26246AL\"></sup> and you chose for a time to enjoy his light.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“I have testimony weightier than that of John.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26247AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26247AM\"></sup> For the works that the Father has given me to finish—the very works that I am doing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26247AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26247AN\"></sup>—testify that the Father has sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26247AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26247AO\"></sup></span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>And the Father who sent me has himself testified concerning me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26248AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26248AP\"></sup> You have never heard his voice nor seen his form,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26248AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26248AQ\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>nor does his word dwell in you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26249AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26249AR\"></sup> for you do not believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26249AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26249AS\"></sup> the one he sent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26249AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26249AT\"></sup></span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>You study the Scriptures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26250AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26250AU\"></sup> diligently because you think that in them you have eternal life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26250AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26250AV\"></sup> These are the very Scriptures that testify about me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26250AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26250AW\"></sup></span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>yet you refuse to come to me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26251AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26251AX\"></sup> to have life.</span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“I do not accept glory from human beings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26252AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26252AY\"></sup></span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>but I know you. I know that you do not have the love of God in your hearts.</span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>I have come in my Father’s name, and you do not accept me; but if someone else comes in his own name, you will accept him.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>How can you believe since you accept glory from one another but do not seek the glory that comes from the only God?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26255AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26255AZ\"></sup></span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“But do not think I will accuse you before the Father. Your accuser is Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26256BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26256BA\"></sup> on whom your hopes are set.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26256BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26256BB\"></sup></span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>If you believed Moses, you would believe me, for he wrote about me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26257BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26257BC\"></sup></span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But since you do not believe what he wrote, how are you going to believe what I say?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26258BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26258BD\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Some time after this, Jesus crossed to the far shore of the Sea of Galilee (that is, the Sea of Tiberias),",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and a great crowd of people followed him because they saw the signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26260B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26260B\"></sup> he had performed by healing the sick.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Jesus went up on a mountainside<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26261C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26261C\"></sup> and sat down with his disciples.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The Jewish Passover Festival<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26262D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26262D\"></sup> was near.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Jesus looked up and saw a great crowd coming toward him, he said to Philip,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26263E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26263E\"></sup> <span class=\"woj\">“Where shall we buy bread for these people to eat?”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He asked this only to test him, for he already had in mind what he was going to do.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Philip answered him, “It would take more than half a year’s wages to buy enough bread for each one to have a bite!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Another of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter’s brother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26266F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26266F\"></sup> spoke up,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Here is a boy with five small barley loaves and two small fish, but how far will they go among so many?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26267G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26267G\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Have the people sit down.”</span> There was plenty of grass in that place, and they sat down (about five thousand men were there).",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jesus then took the loaves, gave thanks,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26269H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26269H\"></sup> and distributed to those who were seated as much as they wanted. He did the same with the fish.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When they had all had enough to eat, he said to his disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“Gather the pieces that are left over. Let nothing be wasted.”</span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So they gathered them and filled twelve baskets with the pieces of the five barley loaves left over by those who had eaten.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After the people saw the sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26272I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26272I\"></sup> Jesus performed, they began to say, “Surely this is the Prophet who is to come into the world.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26272J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26272J\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Jesus, knowing that they intended to come and make him king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26273K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26273K\"></sup> by force, withdrew again to a mountain by himself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26273L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26273L\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When evening came, his disciples went down to the lake,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>where they got into a boat and set off across the lake for Capernaum. By now it was dark, and Jesus had not yet joined them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>A strong wind was blowing and the waters grew rough.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When they had rowed about three or four miles, they saw Jesus approaching the boat, walking on the water;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26277N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26277N\"></sup> and they were frightened.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“It is I; don’t be afraid.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26278O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26278O\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then they were willing to take him into the boat, and immediately the boat reached the shore where they were heading.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The next day the crowd that had stayed on the opposite shore of the lake<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26280P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26280P\"></sup> realized that only one boat had been there, and that Jesus had not entered it with his disciples, but that they had gone away alone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26280Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26280Q\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then some boats from Tiberias<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26281R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26281R\"></sup> landed near the place where the people had eaten the bread after the Lord had given thanks.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26281S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26281S\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Once the crowd realized that neither Jesus nor his disciples were there, they got into the boats and went to Capernaum in search of Jesus.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When they found him on the other side of the lake, they asked him, “Rabbi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26283T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26283T\"></sup> when did you get here?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, you are looking for me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26284U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26284U\"></sup> not because you saw the signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26284V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26284V\"></sup> I performed but because you ate the loaves and had your fill.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Do not work for food that spoils, but for food that endures<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26285W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26285W\"></sup> to eternal life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26285X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26285X\"></sup> which the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26285Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26285Y\"></sup> will give you. For on him God the Father has placed his seal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26285Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26285Z\"></sup> of approval.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then they asked him, “What must we do to do the works God requires?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“The work of God is this: to believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26287AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26287AA\"></sup> in the one he has sent.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26287AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26287AB\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So they asked him, “What sign<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26288AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26288AC\"></sup> then will you give that we may see it and believe you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26288AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26288AD\"></sup> What will you do?",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Our ancestors ate the manna<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26289AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26289AE\"></sup> in the wilderness; as it is written: ‘He gave them bread from heaven to eat.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26289AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26289AF\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, it is not Moses who has given you the bread from heaven, but it is my Father who gives you the true bread from heaven.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>For the bread of God is the bread that comes down from heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26291AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26291AG\"></sup> and gives life to the world.”</span>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Sir,” they said, “always give us this bread.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26292AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26292AH\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then Jesus declared, <span class=\"woj\">“I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26293AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26293AI\"></sup> the bread of life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26293AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26293AJ\"></sup> Whoever comes to me will never go hungry, and whoever believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26293AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26293AK\"></sup> in me will never be thirsty.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26293AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26293AL\"></sup></span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But as I told you, you have seen me and still you do not believe.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>All those the Father gives me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26295AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26295AM\"></sup> will come to me, and whoever comes to me I will never drive away.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>For I have come down from heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26296AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26296AN\"></sup> not to do my will but to do the will<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26296AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26296AO\"></sup> of him who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26296AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26296AP\"></sup></span>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And this is the will of him who sent me, that I shall lose none of all those he has given me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26297AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26297AQ\"></sup> but raise them up at the last day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26297AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26297AR\"></sup></span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>For my Father’s will is that everyone who looks to the Son<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26298AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26298AS\"></sup> and believes in him shall have eternal life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26298AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26298AT\"></sup> and I will raise them up at the last day.”</span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>At this the Jews there began to grumble about him because he said, <span class=\"woj\">“I am the bread that came down from heaven.”</span>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>They said, “Is this not Jesus, the son of Joseph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26300AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26300AU\"></sup> whose father and mother we know?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26300AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26300AV\"></sup> How can he now say, <span class=\"woj\">‘I came down from heaven’</span>?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26300AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26300AW\"></sup>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“Stop grumbling among yourselves,”</span> Jesus answered.",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“No one can come to me unless the Father who sent me draws them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26302AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26302AX\"></sup> and I will raise them up at the last day.</span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>It is written in the Prophets: ‘They will all be taught by God.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26303AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26303AY\"></sup> Everyone who has heard the Father and learned from him comes to me.</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>No one has seen the Father except the one who is from God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26304AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26304AZ\"></sup> only he has seen the Father.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Very truly I tell you, the one who believes has eternal life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26305BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26305BA\"></sup></span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>I am the bread of life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26306BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26306BB\"></sup></span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Your ancestors ate the manna in the wilderness, yet they died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26307BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26307BC\"></sup></span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>But here is the bread that comes down from heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26308BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26308BD\"></sup> which anyone may eat and not die.</span>",
			"51": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>I am the living bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26309BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26309BE\"></sup> that came down from heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26309BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26309BF\"></sup> Whoever eats this bread will live forever. This bread is my flesh, which I will give for the life of the world.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26309BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26309BG\"></sup></span>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>Then the Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26310BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26310BH\"></sup> began to argue sharply among themselves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26310BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26310BI\"></sup> “How can this man give us his flesh to eat?”",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, unless you eat the flesh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26311BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26311BJ\"></sup> of the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26311BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26311BK\"></sup> and drink his blood,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26311BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26311BL\"></sup> you have no life in you.</span>",
			"54": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Whoever eats my flesh and drinks my blood has eternal life, and I will raise them up at the last day.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26312BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26312BM\"></sup></span>",
			"55": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>For my flesh is real food and my blood is real drink.</span>",
			"56": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Whoever eats my flesh and drinks my blood remains in me, and I in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26314BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26314BN\"></sup></span>",
			"57": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>Just as the living Father sent me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26315BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26315BO\"></sup> and I live because of the Father, so the one who feeds on me will live because of me.</span>",
			"58": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>This is the bread that came down from heaven. Your ancestors ate manna and died, but whoever feeds on this bread will live forever.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26316BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26316BP\"></sup></span>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>He said this while teaching in the synagogue in Capernaum.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>On hearing it, many of his disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26318BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26318BQ\"></sup> said, “This is a hard teaching. Who can accept it?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26318BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26318BR\"></sup>",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Aware that his disciples were grumbling about this, Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Does this offend you?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26319BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26319BS\"></sup></span>",
			"62": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>Then what if you see the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26320BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26320BT\"></sup> ascend to where he was before!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26320BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26320BU\"></sup></span>",
			"63": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>The Spirit gives life;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26321BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26321BV\"></sup> the flesh counts for nothing. The words I have spoken to you—they are full of the Spirit and life.</span>",
			"64": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>Yet there are some of you who do not believe.”</span> For Jesus had known<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26322BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26322BW\"></sup> from the beginning which of them did not believe and who would betray him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26322BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26322BX\"></sup>",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>He went on to say, <span class=\"woj\">“This is why I told you that no one can come to me unless the Father has enabled them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26323BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26323BY\"></sup></span>",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>From this time many of his disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26324BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26324BZ\"></sup> turned back and no longer followed him.",
			"67": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>“You do not want to leave too, do you?”</span> Jesus asked the Twelve.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26325CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26325CA\"></sup>",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>Simon Peter answered him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26326CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26326CB\"></sup> “Lord, to whom shall we go? You have the words of eternal life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26326CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26326CC\"></sup>",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>We have come to believe and to know that you are the Holy One of God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26327CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26327CD\"></sup>",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>Then Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Have I not chosen you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26328CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26328CE\"></sup> the Twelve? Yet one of you is a devil!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26328CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26328CF\"></sup></span>",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>(He meant Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26329CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26329CG\"></sup> who, though one of the Twelve, was later to betray him.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26329CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26329CH\"></sup>"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>After this, Jesus went around in Galilee. He did not want to go about in Judea because the Jewish leaders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26330A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26330A\"></sup> there were looking for a way to kill him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26330B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26330B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But when the Jewish Festival of Tabernacles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26331C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26331C\"></sup> was near,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jesus’ brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26332D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26332D\"></sup> said to him, “Leave Galilee and go to Judea, so that your disciples there may see the works you do.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>No one who wants to become a public figure acts in secret. Since you are doing these things, show yourself to the world.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For even his own brothers did not believe in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26334E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26334E\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Therefore Jesus told them, <span class=\"woj\">“My time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26335F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26335F\"></sup> is not yet here; for you any time will do.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The world cannot hate you, but it hates me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26336G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26336G\"></sup> because I testify that its works are evil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26336H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26336H\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You go to the festival. I am not going up to this festival, because my time<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26337I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26337I\"></sup> has not yet fully come.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>After he had said this, he stayed in Galilee.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>However, after his brothers had left for the festival, he went also, not publicly, but in secret.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now at the festival the Jewish leaders were watching for Jesus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26340J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26340J\"></sup> and asking, “Where is he?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Among the crowds there was widespread whispering about him. Some said, “He is a good man.”Others replied, “No, he deceives the people.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26341K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26341K\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But no one would say anything publicly about him for fear of the leaders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26342L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26342L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Not until halfway through the festival did Jesus go up to the temple courts and begin to teach.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26343M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26343M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26344N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26344N\"></sup> there were amazed and asked, “How did this man get such learning<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26344O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26344O\"></sup> without having been taught?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26344P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26344P\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“My teaching is not my own. It comes from the one who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26345Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26345Q\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Anyone who chooses to do the will of God will find out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26346R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26346R\"></sup> whether my teaching comes from God or whether I speak on my own.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whoever speaks on their own does so to gain personal glory,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26347S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26347S\"></sup> but he who seeks the glory of the one who sent him is a man of truth; there is nothing false about him.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Has not Moses given you the law?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26348T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26348T\"></sup> Yet not one of you keeps the law. Why are you trying to kill me?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26348U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26348U\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“You are demon-possessed,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26349V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26349V\"></sup> the crowd answered. “Who is trying to kill you?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I did one miracle,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26350W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26350W\"></sup> and you are all amazed.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Yet, because Moses gave you circumcision<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26351X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26351X\"></sup> (though actually it did not come from Moses, but from the patriarchs),<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26351Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26351Y\"></sup> you circumcise a boy on the Sabbath.</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now if a boy can be circumcised on the Sabbath so that the law of Moses may not be broken, why are you angry with me for healing a man’s whole body on the Sabbath?</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Stop judging by mere appearances, but instead judge correctly.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26353Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26353Z\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>At that point some of the people of Jerusalem began to ask, “Isn’t this the man they are trying to kill?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26354AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26354AA\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Here he is, speaking publicly, and they are not saying a word to him. Have the authorities<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26355AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26355AB\"></sup> really concluded that he is the Messiah?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26355AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26355AC\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But we know where this man is from;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26356AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26356AD\"></sup> when the Messiah comes, no one will know where he is from.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Jesus, still teaching in the temple courts,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26357AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26357AE\"></sup> cried out, <span class=\"woj\">“Yes, you know me, and you know where I am from.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26357AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26357AF\"></sup> I am not here on my own authority, but he who sent me is true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26357AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26357AG\"></sup> You do not know him,</span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>but I know him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26358AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26358AH\"></sup> because I am from him and he sent me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26358AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26358AI\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>At this they tried to seize him, but no one laid a hand on him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26359AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26359AJ\"></sup> because his hour had not yet come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26359AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26359AK\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Still, many in the crowd believed in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26360AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26360AL\"></sup> They said, “When the Messiah comes, will he perform more signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26360AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26360AM\"></sup> than this man?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The Pharisees heard the crowd whispering such things about him. Then the chief priests and the Pharisees sent temple guards to arrest him.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“I am with you for only a short time,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26362AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26362AN\"></sup> and then I am going to the one who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26362AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26362AO\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>You will look for me, but you will not find me; and where I am, you cannot come.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26363AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26363AP\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The Jews said to one another, “Where does this man intend to go that we cannot find him? Will he go where our people live scattered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26364AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26364AQ\"></sup> among the Greeks,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26364AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26364AR\"></sup> and teach the Greeks?",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>What did he mean when he said, <span class=\"woj\">‘You will look for me, but you will not find me,’</span> and <span class=\"woj\">‘Where I am, you cannot come’</span>?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26365AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26365AS\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>On the last and greatest day of the festival,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26366AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26366AT\"></sup> Jesus stood and said in a loud voice, <span class=\"woj\">“Let anyone who is thirsty come to me and drink.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26366AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26366AU\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Whoever believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26367AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26367AV\"></sup> in me, as Scripture has said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26367AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26367AW\"></sup> rivers of living water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26367AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26367AX\"></sup> will flow from within them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26367AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26367AY\"></sup></span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>By this he meant the Spirit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26368AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26368AZ\"></sup> whom those who believed in him were later to receive.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26368BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26368BA\"></sup> Up to that time the Spirit had not been given, since Jesus had not yet been glorified.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26368BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26368BB\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>On hearing his words, some of the people said, “Surely this man is the Prophet.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26369BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26369BC\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Others said, “He is the Messiah.”Still others asked, “How can the Messiah come from Galilee?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26370BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26370BD\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Does not Scripture say that the Messiah will come from David’s descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26371BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26371BE\"></sup> and from Bethlehem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26371BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26371BF\"></sup> the town where David lived?”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Thus the people were divided<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26372BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26372BG\"></sup> because of Jesus.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Some wanted to seize him, but no one laid a hand on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26373BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26373BH\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Finally the temple guards went back to the chief priests and the Pharisees, who asked them, “Why didn’t you bring him in?”",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“No one ever spoke the way this man does,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26375BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26375BI\"></sup> the guards replied.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“You mean he has deceived you also?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26376BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26376BJ\"></sup> the Pharisees retorted.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>“Have any of the rulers or of the Pharisees believed in him?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26377BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26377BK\"></sup>",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>No! But this mob that knows nothing of the law—there is a curse on them.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Nicodemus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26379BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26379BL\"></sup> who had gone to Jesus earlier and who was one of their own number, asked,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>“Does our law condemn a man without first hearing him to find out what he has been doing?”",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>They replied, “Are you from Galilee, too? Look into it, and you will find that a prophet does not come out of Galilee.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26381BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26381BM\"></sup>[The earliest manuscripts and many other ancient witnesses do not have John 7:53—8:11. A few manuscripts include these verses, wholly or in part, after John 7:36, John 21:25, Luke 21:38 or Luke 24:53.]",
			"53": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Then they all went home,</i>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">8 </span><i><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>but Jesus went to the Mount of Olives.</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26383A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26383A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>At dawn he appeared again in the temple courts, where all the people gathered around him, and he sat down to teach them.</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26384B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26384B\"></sup>",
			"3": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The teachers of the law and the Pharisees brought in a woman caught in adultery. They made her stand before the group</i>",
			"4": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and said to Jesus, “Teacher, this woman was caught in the act of adultery.</i>",
			"5": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the Law Moses commanded us to stone such women.</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26387C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26387C\"></sup> <i>Now what do you say?”</i>",
			"6": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They were using this question as a trap,</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26388D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26388D\"></sup> <i>in order to have a basis for accusing him.</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26388E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26388E\"></sup><i>But Jesus bent down and started to write on the ground with his finger.</i>",
			"7": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When they kept on questioning him, he straightened up and said to them, “Let any one of you who is without sin be the first to throw a stone</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26389F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26389F\"></sup> <i>at her.”</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26389G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26389G\"></sup>",
			"8": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Again he stooped down and wrote on the ground.</i>",
			"9": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>At this, those who heard began to go away one at a time, the older ones first, until only Jesus was left, with the woman still standing there.</i>",
			"10": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jesus straightened up and asked her, “Woman, where are they? Has no one condemned you?”</i>",
			"11": "<i><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“No one, sir,” she said.</i><i>“Then neither do I condemn you,”</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26393H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26393H\"></sup> <i>Jesus declared. “Go now and leave your life of sin.”</i><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26393I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26393I\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Jesus spoke again to the people, he said, <span class=\"woj\">“I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26394J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26394J\"></sup> the light of the world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26394K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26394K\"></sup> Whoever follows me will never walk in darkness, but will have the light of life.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26394L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26394L\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The Pharisees challenged him, “Here you are, appearing as your own witness; your testimony is not valid.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26395M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26395M\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Even if I testify on my own behalf, my testimony is valid, for I know where I came from and where I am going.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26396N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26396N\"></sup> But you have no idea where I come from<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26396O\"></sup> or where I am going.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You judge by human standards;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26397P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26397P\"></sup> I pass judgment on no one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26397Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26397Q\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But if I do judge, my decisions are true, because I am not alone. I stand with the Father, who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26398R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26398R\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In your own Law it is written that the testimony of two witnesses is true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26399S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26399S\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I am one who testifies for myself; my other witness is the Father, who sent me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26400T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26400T\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then they asked him, “Where is your father?”<span class=\"woj\">“You do not know me or my Father,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26401U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26401U\"></sup></span> Jesus replied. <span class=\"woj\">“If you knew me, you would know my Father also.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26401V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26401V\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He spoke these words while teaching<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26402W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26402W\"></sup> in the temple courts near the place where the offerings were put.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26402X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26402X\"></sup> Yet no one seized him, because his hour had not yet come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26402Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26402Y\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Once more Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I am going away, and you will look for me, and you will die<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26403Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26403Z\"></sup> in your sin. Where I go, you cannot come.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26403AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26403AA\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>This made the Jews ask, “Will he kill himself? Is that why he says, <span class=\"woj\">‘Where I go, you cannot come’</span>?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But he continued, <span class=\"woj\">“You are from below; I am from above. You are of this world; I am not of this world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26405AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26405AB\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I told you that you would die in your sins; if you do not believe that I am he,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26406AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26406AC\"></sup> you will indeed die in your sins.”</span>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Who are you?” they asked.<span class=\"woj\">“Just what I have been telling you from the beginning,”</span> Jesus replied.",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“I have much to say in judgment of you. But he who sent me is trustworthy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26408AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26408AD\"></sup> and what I have heard from him I tell the world.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26408AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26408AE\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They did not understand that he was telling them about his Father.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“When you have lifted up the Son of Man,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26410AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26410AF\"></sup> then you will know that I am he and that I do nothing on my own but speak just what the Father has taught me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26410AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26410AG\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The one who sent me is with me; he has not left me alone,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26411AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26411AH\"></sup> for I always do what pleases him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26411AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26411AI\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Even as he spoke, many believed in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26412AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26412AJ\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>To the Jews who had believed him, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“If you hold to my teaching,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26413AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26413AK\"></sup> you are really my disciples.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26414AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26414AL\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They answered him, “We are Abraham’s descendants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26415AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26415AM\"></sup> and have never been slaves of anyone. How can you say that we shall be set free?”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, everyone who sins is a slave to sin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26416AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26416AN\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Now a slave has no permanent place in the family, but a son belongs to it forever.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26417AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26417AO\"></sup></span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So if the Son sets you free,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26418AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26418AP\"></sup> you will be free indeed.</span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>I know that you are Abraham’s descendants. Yet you are looking for a way to kill me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26419AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26419AQ\"></sup> because you have no room for my word.</span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>I am telling you what I have seen in the Father’s presence,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26420AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26420AR\"></sup> and you are doing what you have heard from your father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26420AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26420AS\"></sup></span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“Abraham is our father,” they answered.<span class=\"woj\">“If you were Abraham’s children,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26421AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26421AT\"></sup></span> said Jesus, <span class=\"woj\">“then you would do what Abraham did.</span>",
			"40": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>As it is, you are looking for a way to kill me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26422AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26422AU\"></sup> a man who has told you the truth that I heard from God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26422AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26422AV\"></sup> Abraham did not do such things.</span>",
			"41": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You are doing the works of your own father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26423AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26423AW\"></sup></span>“We are not illegitimate children,” they protested. “The only Father we have is God himself.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26423AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26423AX\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“If God were your Father, you would love me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26424AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26424AY\"></sup> for I have come here from God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26424AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26424AZ\"></sup> I have not come on my own;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26424BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26424BA\"></sup> God sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26424BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26424BB\"></sup></span>",
			"43": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Why is my language not clear to you? Because you are unable to hear what I say.</span>",
			"44": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>You belong to your father, the devil,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26426BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26426BC\"></sup> and you want to carry out your father’s desires.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26426BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26426BD\"></sup> He was a murderer from the beginning, not holding to the truth, for there is no truth in him. When he lies, he speaks his native language, for he is a liar and the father of lies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26426BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26426BE\"></sup></span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Yet because I tell the truth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26427BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26427BF\"></sup> you do not believe me!</span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>Can any of you prove me guilty of sin? If I am telling the truth, why don’t you believe me?</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Whoever belongs to God hears what God says.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26429BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26429BG\"></sup> The reason you do not hear is that you do not belong to God.”</span>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>The Jews answered him, “Aren’t we right in saying that you are a Samaritan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26430BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26430BH\"></sup> and demon-possessed?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26430BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26430BI\"></sup>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>“I am not possessed by a demon,”</span> said Jesus, <span class=\"woj\">“but I honor my Father and you dishonor me.</span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>I am not seeking glory for myself;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26432BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26432BJ\"></sup> but there is one who seeks it, and he is the judge.</span>",
			"51": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>Very truly I tell you, whoever obeys my word will never see death.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26433BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26433BK\"></sup></span>",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>At this they exclaimed, “Now we know that you are demon-possessed!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26434BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26434BL\"></sup> Abraham died and so did the prophets, yet you say that whoever obeys your word will never taste death.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>Are you greater than our father Abraham?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26435BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26435BM\"></sup> He died, and so did the prophets. Who do you think you are?”",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“If I glorify myself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26436BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26436BN\"></sup> my glory means nothing. My Father, whom you claim as your God, is the one who glorifies me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26436BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26436BO\"></sup></span>",
			"55": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>Though you do not know him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26437BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26437BP\"></sup> I know him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26437BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26437BQ\"></sup> If I said I did not, I would be a liar like you, but I do know him and obey his word.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26437BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26437BR\"></sup></span>",
			"56": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>Your father Abraham<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26438BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26438BS\"></sup> rejoiced at the thought of seeing my day; he saw it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26438BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26438BT\"></sup> and was glad.”</span>",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>“You are not yet fifty years old,” they said to him, “and you have seen Abraham!”",
			"58": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>“Very truly I tell you,”</span> Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“before Abraham was born,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26440BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26440BU\"></sup> I am!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26440BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26440BV\"></sup></span>",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>At this, they picked up stones to stone him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26441BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26441BW\"></sup> but Jesus hid himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26441BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26441BX\"></sup> slipping away from the temple grounds."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>As he went along, he saw a man blind from birth.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>His disciples asked him, “Rabbi,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26443A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26443A\"></sup> who sinned,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26443B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26443B\"></sup> this man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26443C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26443C\"></sup> or his parents,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26443D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26443D\"></sup> that he was born blind?”",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Neither this man nor his parents sinned,”</span> said Jesus, <span class=\"woj\">“but this happened so that the works of God might be displayed in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26444E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26444E\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As long as it is day,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26445F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26445F\"></sup> we must do the works of him who sent me. Night is coming, when no one can work.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>While I am in the world, I am the light of the world.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26446G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26446G\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>After saying this, he spit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26447H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26447H\"></sup> on the ground, made some mud with the saliva, and put it on the man’s eyes.",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Go,”</span> he told him, <span class=\"woj\">“wash in the Pool of Siloam”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26448I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26448I\"></sup></span> (this word means “Sent”). So the man went and washed, and came home seeing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26448J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26448J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>His neighbors and those who had formerly seen him begging asked, “Isn’t this the same man who used to sit and beg?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26449K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26449K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Some claimed that he was.Others said, “No, he only looks like him.”But he himself insisted, “I am the man.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“How then were your eyes opened?” they asked.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He replied, “The man they call Jesus made some mud and put it on my eyes. He told me to go to Siloam and wash. So I went and washed, and then I could see.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26452L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26452L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Where is this man?” they asked him.“I don’t know,” he said.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They brought to the Pharisees the man who had been blind.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now the day on which Jesus had made the mud and opened the man’s eyes was a Sabbath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26455M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26455M\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Therefore the Pharisees also asked him how he had received his sight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26456N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26456N\"></sup> “He put mud on my eyes,” the man replied, “and I washed, and now I see.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Some of the Pharisees said, “This man is not from God, for he does not keep the Sabbath.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26457O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26457O\"></sup>But others asked, “How can a sinner perform such signs?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26457P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26457P\"></sup> So they were divided.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26457Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26457Q\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then they turned again to the blind man, “What have you to say about him? It was your eyes he opened.”The man replied, “He is a prophet.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26458R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26458R\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26459S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26459S\"></sup> still did not believe that he had been blind and had received his sight until they sent for the man’s parents.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Is this your son?” they asked. “Is this the one you say was born blind? How is it that now he can see?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“We know he is our son,” the parents answered, “and we know he was born blind.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But how he can see now, or who opened his eyes, we don’t know. Ask him. He is of age; he will speak for himself.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>His parents said this because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26463T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26463T\"></sup> who already had decided that anyone who acknowledged that Jesus was the Messiah would be put out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26463U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26463U\"></sup> of the synagogue.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26463V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26463V\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>That was why his parents said, “He is of age; ask him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26464W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26464W\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>A second time they summoned the man who had been blind. “Give glory to God by telling the truth,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26465X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26465X\"></sup> they said. “We know this man is a sinner.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26465Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26465Y\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He replied, “Whether he is a sinner or not, I don’t know. One thing I do know. I was blind but now I see!”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then they asked him, “What did he do to you? How did he open your eyes?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He answered, “I have told you already<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26468Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26468Z\"></sup> and you did not listen. Why do you want to hear it again? Do you want to become his disciples too?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then they hurled insults at him and said, “You are this fellow’s disciple! We are disciples of Moses!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26469AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26469AA\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>We know that God spoke to Moses, but as for this fellow, we don’t even know where he comes from.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26470AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26470AB\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The man answered, “Now that is remarkable! You don’t know where he comes from, yet he opened my eyes.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>We know that God does not listen to sinners. He listens to the godly person who does his will.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26472AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26472AC\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Nobody has ever heard of opening the eyes of a man born blind.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>If this man were not from God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26474AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26474AD\"></sup> he could do nothing.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>To this they replied, “You were steeped in sin at birth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26475AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26475AE\"></sup> how dare you lecture us!” And they threw him out.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26475AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26475AF\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jesus heard that they had thrown him out, and when he found him, he said, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26476AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26476AG\"></sup> in the Son of Man?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26476AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26476AH\"></sup></span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“Who is he, sir?” the man asked. “Tell me so that I may believe in him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26477AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26477AI\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“You have now seen him; in fact, he is the one speaking with you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26478AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26478AJ\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then the man said, “Lord, I believe,” and he worshiped him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26479AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26479AK\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“For judgment<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26480AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26480AL\"></sup> I have come into this world,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26480AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26480AM\"></sup> so that the blind will see<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26480AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26480AN\"></sup> and those who see will become blind.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26480AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26480AO\"></sup></span>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Some Pharisees who were with him heard him say this and asked, “What? Are we blind too?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26481AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26481AP\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“If you were blind, you would not be guilty of sin; but now that you claim you can see, your guilt remains.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26482AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26482AQ\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you Pharisees, anyone who does not enter the sheep pen by the gate, but climbs in by some other way, is a thief and a robber.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26483A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26483A\"></sup></span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The one who enters by the gate is the shepherd of the sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26484B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26484B\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, and the sheep listen to his voice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26485C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26485C\"></sup> He calls his own sheep by name and leads them out.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26485D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26485D\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When he has brought out all his own, he goes on ahead of them, and his sheep follow him because they know his voice.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26486E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26486E\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But they will never follow a stranger; in fact, they will run away from him because they do not recognize a stranger’s voice.”</span>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jesus used this figure of speech,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26488F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26488F\"></sup> but the Pharisees did not understand what he was telling them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26488G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26488G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Therefore Jesus said again, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26489H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26489H\"></sup> the gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26489I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26489I\"></sup> for the sheep.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>All who have come before me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26490J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26490J\"></sup> are thieves and robbers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26490K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26490K\"></sup> but the sheep have not listened to them.</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I am the gate; whoever enters through me will be saved. They will come in and go out, and find pasture.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy; I have come that they may have life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26492L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26492L\"></sup> and have it to the full.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26492M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26492M\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26493N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26493N\"></sup> the good shepherd.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26493O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26493O\"></sup> The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26493P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26493P\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The hired hand is not the shepherd and does not own the sheep. So when he sees the wolf coming, he abandons the sheep and runs away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26494Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26494Q\"></sup> Then the wolf attacks the flock and scatters it.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The man runs away because he is a hired hand and cares nothing for the sheep.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“I am the good shepherd;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26496R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26496R\"></sup> I know my sheep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26496S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26496S\"></sup> and my sheep know me—</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>just as the Father knows me and I know the Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26497T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26497T\"></sup>—and I lay down my life for the sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26497U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26497U\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I have other sheep<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26498V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26498V\"></sup> that are not of this sheep pen. I must bring them also. They too will listen to my voice, and there shall be one flock<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26498W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26498W\"></sup> and one shepherd.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26498X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26498X\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The reason my Father loves me is that I lay down my life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26499Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26499Y\"></sup>—only to take it up again.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>No one takes it from me, but I lay it down of my own accord.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26500Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26500Z\"></sup> I have authority to lay it down and authority to take it up again. This command I received from my Father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26500AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26500AA\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The Jews who heard these words were again divided.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26501AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26501AB\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Many of them said, “He is demon-possessed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26502AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26502AC\"></sup> and raving mad.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26502AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26502AD\"></sup> Why listen to him?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But others said, “These are not the sayings of a man possessed by a demon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26503AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26503AE\"></sup> Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26503AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26503AF\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then came the Festival of Dedication at Jerusalem. It was winter,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and Jesus was in the temple courts walking in Solomon’s Colonnade.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26505AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26505AG\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The Jews<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26506AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26506AH\"></sup> who were there gathered around him, saying, “How long will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Messiah, tell us plainly.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26506AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26506AI\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“I did tell you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26507AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26507AJ\"></sup> but you do not believe. The works I do in my Father’s name testify about me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26507AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26507AK\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>but you do not believe because you are not my sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26508AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26508AL\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>My sheep listen to my voice; I know them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26509AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26509AM\"></sup> and they follow me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26509AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26509AN\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I give them eternal life,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26510AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26510AO\"></sup> and they shall never perish;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26510AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26510AP\"></sup> no one will snatch them out of my hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26510AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26510AQ\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>My Father, who has given them to me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26511AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26511AR\"></sup> is greater than all;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26511AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26511AS\"></sup> no one can snatch them out of my Father’s hand.</span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I and the Father are one.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26512AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26512AT\"></sup></span>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Again his Jewish opponents picked up stones to stone him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26513AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26513AU\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>but Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“I have shown you many good works from the Father. For which of these do you stone me?”</span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“We are not stoning you for any good work,” they replied, “but for blasphemy, because you, a mere man, claim to be God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26515AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26515AV\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Jesus answered them, <span class=\"woj\">“Is it not written in your Law,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26516AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26516AW\"></sup> ‘I have said you are “gods”’?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26516AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26516AX\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>If he called them ‘gods,’ to whom the word of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26517AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26517AY\"></sup> came—and Scripture cannot be set aside<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26517AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26517AZ\"></sup>—</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>what about the one whom the Father set apart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26518BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26518BA\"></sup> as his very own<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26518BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26518BB\"></sup> and sent into the world?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26518BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26518BC\"></sup> Why then do you accuse me of blasphemy because I said, ‘I am God’s Son’?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26518BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26518BD\"></sup></span>",
			"37": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Do not believe me unless I do the works of my Father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26519BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26519BE\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>But if I do them, even though you do not believe me, believe the works, that you may know and understand that the Father is in me, and I in the Father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26520BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26520BF\"></sup></span>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Again they tried to seize him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26521BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26521BG\"></sup> but he escaped their grasp.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26521BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26521BH\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Jesus went back across the Jordan<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26522BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26522BI\"></sup> to the place where John had been baptizing in the early days. There he stayed,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>and many people came to him. They said, “Though John never performed a sign,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26523BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26523BJ\"></sup> all that John said about this man was true.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26523BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26523BK\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>And in that place many believed in Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26524BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26524BL\"></sup>"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now a man named Lazarus was sick. He was from Bethany,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26525A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26525A\"></sup> the village of Mary and her sister Martha.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26525B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26525B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>(This Mary, whose brother Lazarus now lay sick, was the same one who poured perfume on the Lord and wiped his feet with her hair.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26526C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26526C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the sisters sent word to Jesus, “Lord, the one you love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26527D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26527D\"></sup> is sick.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When he heard this, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“This sickness will not end in death. No, it is for God’s glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26528E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26528E\"></sup> so that God’s Son may be glorified through it.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now Jesus loved Martha and her sister and Lazarus.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So when he heard that Lazarus was sick, he stayed where he was two more days,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and then he said to his disciples, <span class=\"woj\">“Let us go back to Judea.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26531F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26531F\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“But Rabbi,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26532G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26532G\"></sup> they said, “a short while ago the Jews there tried to stone you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26532H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26532H\"></sup> and yet you are going back?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Are there not twelve hours of daylight? Anyone who walks in the daytime will not stumble, for they see by this world’s light.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26533I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26533I\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It is when a person walks at night that they stumble, for they have no light.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>After he had said this, he went on to tell them, <span class=\"woj\">“Our friend<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26535J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26535J\"></sup> Lazarus has fallen asleep;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26535K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26535K\"></sup> but I am going there to wake him up.”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>His disciples replied, “Lord, if he sleeps, he will get better.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesus had been speaking of his death, but his disciples thought he meant natural sleep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26537L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26537L\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So then he told them plainly, <span class=\"woj\">“Lazarus is dead,</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and for your sake I am glad I was not there, so that you may believe. But let us go to him.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Thomas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26540M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26540M\"></sup> (also known as Didymus) said to the rest of the disciples, “Let us also go, that we may die with him.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>On his arrival, Jesus found that Lazarus had already been in the tomb for four days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26541N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26541N\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Bethany<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26542O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26542O\"></sup> was less than two miles from Jerusalem,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and many Jews had come to Martha and Mary to comfort them in the loss of their brother.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26543P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26543P\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When Martha heard that Jesus was coming, she went out to meet him, but Mary stayed at home.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26544Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26544Q\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“Lord,” Martha said to Jesus, “if you had been here, my brother would not have died.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26545R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26545R\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But I know that even now God will give you whatever you ask.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26546S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26546S\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Jesus said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Your brother will rise again.”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Martha answered, “I know he will rise again in the resurrection<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26548T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26548T\"></sup> at the last day.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26548U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26548U\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jesus said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26549V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26549V\"></sup> the resurrection and the life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26549W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26549W\"></sup> The one who believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26549X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26549X\"></sup> in me will live, even though they die;</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and whoever lives by believing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26550Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26550Y\"></sup> in me will never die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26550Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26550Z\"></sup> Do you believe this?”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Yes, Lord,” she replied, “I believe that you are the Messiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26551AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26551AA\"></sup> the Son of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26551AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26551AB\"></sup> who is to come into the world.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26551AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26551AC\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>After she had said this, she went back and called her sister Mary aside. “The Teacher<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26552AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26552AD\"></sup> is here,” she said, “and is asking for you.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>When Mary heard this, she got up quickly and went to him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now Jesus had not yet entered the village, but was still at the place where Martha had met him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26554AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26554AE\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When the Jews who had been with Mary in the house, comforting her,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26555AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26555AF\"></sup> noticed how quickly she got up and went out, they followed her, supposing she was going to the tomb to mourn there.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When Mary reached the place where Jesus was and saw him, she fell at his feet and said, “Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26556AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26556AG\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Jesus saw her weeping, and the Jews who had come along with her also weeping, he was deeply moved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26557AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26557AH\"></sup> in spirit and troubled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26557AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26557AI\"></sup>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Where have you laid him?”</span> he asked.“Come and see, Lord,” they replied.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jesus wept.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26559AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26559AJ\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then the Jews said, “See how he loved him!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26560AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26560AK\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>But some of them said, “Could not he who opened the eyes of the blind man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26561AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26561AL\"></sup> have kept this man from dying?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26561AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26561AM\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Jesus, once more deeply moved,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26562AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26562AN\"></sup> came to the tomb. It was a cave with a stone laid across the entrance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26562AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26562AO\"></sup>",
			"39": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“Take away the stone,”</span> he said.“But, Lord,” said Martha, the sister of the dead man, “by this time there is a bad odor, for he has been there four days.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26563AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26563AP\"></sup>",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Then Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Did I not tell you that if you believe,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26564AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26564AQ\"></sup> you will see the glory of God?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26564AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26564AR\"></sup></span>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>So they took away the stone. Then Jesus looked up<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26565AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26565AS\"></sup> and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26565AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26565AT\"></sup> I thank you that you have heard me.</span>",
			"42": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>I knew that you always hear me, but I said this for the benefit of the people standing here,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26566AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26566AU\"></sup> that they may believe that you sent me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26566AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26566AV\"></sup></span>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>When he had said this, Jesus called in a loud voice, <span class=\"woj\">“Lazarus, come out!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26567AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26567AW\"></sup></span>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The dead man came out, his hands and feet wrapped with strips of linen,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26568AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26568AX\"></sup> and a cloth around his face.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26568AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26568AY\"></sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Take off the grave clothes and let him go.”</span>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>Therefore many of the Jews who had come to visit Mary,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26569AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26569AZ\"></sup> and had seen what Jesus did,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26569BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26569BA\"></sup> believed in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26569BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26569BB\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>But some of them went to the Pharisees and told them what Jesus had done.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Then the chief priests and the Pharisees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26571BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26571BC\"></sup> called a meeting<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26571BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26571BD\"></sup> of the Sanhedrin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26571BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26571BE\"></sup>“What are we accomplishing?” they asked. “Here is this man performing many signs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26571BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26571BF\"></sup>",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>If we let him go on like this, everyone will believe in him, and then the Romans will come and take away both our temple and our nation.”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Then one of them, named Caiaphas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26573BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26573BG\"></sup> who was high priest that year,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26573BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26573BH\"></sup> spoke up, “You know nothing at all!",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>You do not realize that it is better for you that one man die for the people than that the whole nation perish.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26574BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26574BI\"></sup>",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>He did not say this on his own, but as high priest that year he prophesied that Jesus would die for the Jewish nation,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>and not only for that nation but also for the scattered children of God, to bring them together and make them one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26576BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26576BJ\"></sup>",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>So from that day on they plotted to take his life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26577BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26577BK\"></sup>",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>Therefore Jesus no longer moved about publicly among the people of Judea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26578BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26578BL\"></sup> Instead he withdrew to a region near the wilderness, to a village called Ephraim, where he stayed with his disciples.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>When it was almost time for the Jewish Passover,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26579BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26579BM\"></sup> many went up from the country to Jerusalem for their ceremonial cleansing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26579BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26579BN\"></sup> before the Passover.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>They kept looking for Jesus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26580BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26580BO\"></sup> and as they stood in the temple courts they asked one another, “What do you think? Isn’t he coming to the festival at all?”",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>But the chief priests and the Pharisees had given orders that anyone who found out where Jesus was should report it so that they might arrest him."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Six days before the Passover,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26582B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26582B\"></sup> Jesus came to Bethany,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26582C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26582C\"></sup> where Lazarus lived, whom Jesus had raised from the dead.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Here a dinner was given in Jesus’ honor. Martha served,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26583D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26583D\"></sup> while Lazarus was among those reclining at the table with him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Mary took about a pint of pure nard, an expensive perfume;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26584E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26584E\"></sup> she poured it on Jesus’ feet and wiped his feet with her hair.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26584F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26584F\"></sup> And the house was filled with the fragrance of the perfume.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But one of his disciples, Judas Iscariot, who was later to betray him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26585G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26585G\"></sup> objected,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Why wasn’t this perfume sold and the money given to the poor? It was worth a year’s wages.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He did not say this because he cared about the poor but because he was a thief; as keeper of the money bag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26587H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26587H\"></sup> he used to help himself to what was put into it.",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Leave her alone,”</span> Jesus replied. <span class=\"woj\">“It was intended that she should save this perfume for the day of my burial.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26588I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26588I\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You will always have the poor among you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26589J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26589J\"></sup> but you will not always have me.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Meanwhile a large crowd of Jews found out that Jesus was there and came, not only because of him but also to see Lazarus, whom he had raised from the dead.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26590K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26590K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the chief priests made plans to kill Lazarus as well,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>for on account of him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26592L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26592L\"></sup> many of the Jews were going over to Jesus and believing in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26592M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26592M\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The next day the great crowd that had come for the festival heard that Jesus was on his way to Jerusalem.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They took palm branches<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26594O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26594O\"></sup> and went out to meet him, shouting,“Hosanna!”“Blessed is he who comes in the name of the Lord!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26594P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26594P\"></sup>“Blessed is the king of Israel!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26594Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26594Q\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jesus found a young donkey and sat on it, as it is written:",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Do not be afraid, Daughter Zion;see, your king is coming,seated on a donkey’s colt.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26596R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26596R\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>At first his disciples did not understand all this.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26597S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26597S\"></sup> Only after Jesus was glorified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26597T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26597T\"></sup> did they realize that these things had been written about him and that these things had been done to him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now the crowd that was with him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26598U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26598U\"></sup> when he called Lazarus from the tomb and raised him from the dead continued to spread the word.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Many people, because they had heard that he had performed this sign,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26599V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26599V\"></sup> went out to meet him.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So the Pharisees said to one another, “See, this is getting us nowhere. Look how the whole world has gone after him!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26600W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26600W\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now there were some Greeks<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26601X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26601X\"></sup> among those who went up to worship at the festival.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They came to Philip, who was from Bethsaida<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26602Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26602Y\"></sup> in Galilee, with a request. “Sir,” they said, “we would like to see Jesus.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Philip went to tell Andrew; Andrew and Philip in turn told Jesus.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“The hour<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26604Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26604Z\"></sup> has come for the Son of Man to be glorified.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26604AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26604AA\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Very truly I tell you, unless a kernel of wheat falls to the ground and dies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26605AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26605AB\"></sup> it remains only a single seed. But if it dies, it produces many seeds.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Anyone who loves their life will lose it, while anyone who hates their life in this world will keep it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26606AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26606AC\"></sup> for eternal life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26606AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26606AD\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Whoever serves me must follow me; and where I am, my servant also will be.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26607AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26607AE\"></sup> My Father will honor the one who serves me.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“Now my soul is troubled,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26608AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26608AF\"></sup> and what shall I say? ‘Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26608AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26608AG\"></sup> save me from this hour’?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26608AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26608AH\"></sup> No, it was for this very reason I came to this hour.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Father, glorify your name!”</span>Then a voice came from heaven,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26609AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26609AI\"></sup> “I have glorified it, and will glorify it again.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The crowd that was there and heard it said it had thundered; others said an angel had spoken to him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“This voice was for your benefit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26611AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26611AJ\"></sup> not mine.</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now is the time for judgment on this world;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26612AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26612AK\"></sup> now the prince of this world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26612AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26612AL\"></sup> will be driven out.</span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And I, when I am lifted up from the earth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26613AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26613AM\"></sup> will draw all people to myself.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26613AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26613AN\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He said this to show the kind of death he was going to die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26614AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26614AO\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The crowd spoke up, “We have heard from the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26615AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26615AP\"></sup> that the Messiah will remain forever,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26615AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26615AQ\"></sup> so how can you say, <span class=\"woj\">‘The Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26615AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26615AR\"></sup> must be lifted up’</span>?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26615AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26615AS\"></sup> Who is this ‘Son of Man’?”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then Jesus told them, <span class=\"woj\">“You are going to have the light<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26616AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26616AT\"></sup> just a little while longer. Walk while you have the light,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26616AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26616AU\"></sup> before darkness overtakes you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26616AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26616AV\"></sup> Whoever walks in the dark does not know where they are going.</span>",
			"36": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Believe in the light while you have the light, so that you may become children of light.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26617AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26617AW\"></sup></span> When he had finished speaking, Jesus left and hid himself from them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26617AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26617AX\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Even after Jesus had performed so many signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26618AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26618AY\"></sup> in their presence, they still would not believe in him.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>This was to fulfill the word of Isaiah the prophet:“Lord, who has believed our messageand to whom has the arm of the Lord been revealed?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26619AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26619AZ\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>For this reason they could not believe, because, as Isaiah says elsewhere:",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“He has blinded their eyesand hardened their hearts,so they can neither see with their eyes,nor understand with their hearts,nor turn—and I would heal them.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26621BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26621BA\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Isaiah said this because he saw Jesus’ glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26622BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26622BB\"></sup> and spoke about him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26622BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26622BC\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Yet at the same time many even among the leaders believed in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26623BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26623BD\"></sup> But because of the Pharisees<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26623BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26623BE\"></sup> they would not openly acknowledge their faith for fear they would be put out of the synagogue;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26623BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26623BF\"></sup>",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>for they loved human praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26624BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26624BG\"></sup> more than praise from God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26624BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26624BH\"></sup>",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Then Jesus cried out, <span class=\"woj\">“Whoever believes in me does not believe in me only, but in the one who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26625BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26625BI\"></sup></span>",
			"45": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The one who looks at me is seeing the one who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26626BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26626BJ\"></sup></span>",
			"46": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>I have come into the world as a light,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26627BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26627BK\"></sup> so that no one who believes in me should stay in darkness.</span>",
			"47": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“If anyone hears my words but does not keep them, I do not judge that person. For I did not come to judge the world, but to save the world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26628BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26628BL\"></sup></span>",
			"48": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>There is a judge for the one who rejects me and does not accept my words; the very words I have spoken will condemn them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26629BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26629BM\"></sup> at the last day.</span>",
			"49": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>For I did not speak on my own, but the Father who sent me commanded me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26630BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26630BN\"></sup> to say all that I have spoken.</span>",
			"50": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>I know that his command leads to eternal life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26631BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26631BO\"></sup> So whatever I say is just what the Father has told me to say.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26631BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26631BP\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>It was just before the Passover Festival.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26632A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26632A\"></sup> Jesus knew that the hour had come<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26632B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26632B\"></sup> for him to leave this world and go to the Father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26632C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26632C\"></sup> Having loved his own who were in the world, he loved them to the end.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The evening meal was in progress, and the devil had already prompted Judas, the son of Simon Iscariot, to betray Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26633D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26633D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Jesus knew that the Father had put all things under his power,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26634E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26634E\"></sup> and that he had come from God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26634F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26634F\"></sup> and was returning to God;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>so he got up from the meal, took off his outer clothing, and wrapped a towel around his waist.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26635G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26635G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>After that, he poured water into a basin and began to wash his disciples’ feet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26636H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26636H\"></sup> drying them with the towel that was wrapped around him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He came to Simon Peter, who said to him, “Lord, are you going to wash my feet?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“You do not realize now what I am doing, but later you will understand.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26638I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26638I\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“No,” said Peter, “you shall never wash my feet.”Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Unless I wash you, you have no part with me.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Then, Lord,” Simon Peter replied, “not just my feet but my hands and my head as well!”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Those who have had a bath need only to wash their feet; their whole body is clean. And you are clean,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26641J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26641J\"></sup> though not every one of you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26641K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26641K\"></sup></span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For he knew who was going to betray him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26642L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26642L\"></sup> and that was why he said not every one was clean.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When he had finished washing their feet, he put on his clothes and returned to his place. <span class=\"woj\">“Do you understand what I have done for you?”</span> he asked them.",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You call me ‘Teacher’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26644M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26644M\"></sup> and ‘Lord,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26644N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26644N\"></sup> and rightly so, for that is what I am.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now that I, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you also should wash one another’s feet.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26645O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26645O\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I have set you an example that you should do as I have done for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26646P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26646P\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Very truly I tell you, no servant is greater than his master,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26647Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26647Q\"></sup> nor is a messenger greater than the one who sent him.</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now that you know these things, you will be blessed if you do them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26648R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26648R\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“I am not referring to all of you;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26649S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26649S\"></sup> I know those I have chosen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26649T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26649T\"></sup> But this is to fulfill this passage of Scripture:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26649U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26649U\"></sup> ‘He who shared my bread<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26649V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26649V\"></sup> has turned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26649W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26649W\"></sup> against me.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26649X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26649X\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“I am telling you now before it happens, so that when it does happen you will believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26650Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26650Y\"></sup> that I am who I am.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26650Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26650Z\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Very truly I tell you, whoever accepts anyone I send accepts me; and whoever accepts me accepts the one who sent me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26651AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26651AA\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After he had said this, Jesus was troubled in spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26652AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26652AB\"></sup> and testified, <span class=\"woj\">“Very truly I tell you, one of you is going to betray me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26652AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26652AC\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>His disciples stared at one another, at a loss to know which of them he meant.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>One of them, the disciple whom Jesus loved,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26654AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26654AD\"></sup> was reclining next to him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Simon Peter motioned to this disciple and said, “Ask him which one he means.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Leaning back against Jesus, he asked him, “Lord, who is it?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26656AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26656AE\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“It is the one to whom I will give this piece of bread when I have dipped it in the dish.”</span> Then, dipping the piece of bread, he gave it to Judas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26657AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26657AF\"></sup> the son of Simon Iscariot.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>As soon as Judas took the bread, Satan entered into him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26658AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26658AG\"></sup>So Jesus told him, <span class=\"woj\">“What you are about to do, do quickly.”</span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But no one at the meal understood why Jesus said this to him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Since Judas had charge of the money,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26660AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26660AH\"></sup> some thought Jesus was telling him to buy what was needed for the festival,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26660AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26660AI\"></sup> or to give something to the poor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26660AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26660AJ\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>As soon as Judas had taken the bread, he went out. And it was night.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26661AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26661AK\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When he was gone, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Now the Son of Man<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26662AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26662AM\"></sup> is glorified<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26662AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26662AN\"></sup> and God is glorified in him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26662AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26662AO\"></sup></span>",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>If God is glorified in him, God will glorify the Son in himself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26663AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26663AP\"></sup> and will glorify him at once.</span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“My children, I will be with you only a little longer. You will look for me, and just as I told the Jews, so I tell you now: Where I am going, you cannot come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26664AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26664AQ\"></sup></span>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“A new command<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26665AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26665AR\"></sup> I give you: Love one another.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26665AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26665AS\"></sup> As I have loved you, so you must love one another.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26665AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26665AT\"></sup></span>",
			"35": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>By this everyone will know that you are my disciples, if you love one another.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26666AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26666AU\"></sup></span>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Simon Peter asked him, “Lord, where are you going?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26667AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26667AV\"></sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Where I am going, you cannot follow now,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26667AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26667AW\"></sup> but you will follow later.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26667AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26667AX\"></sup></span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Peter asked, “Lord, why can’t I follow you now? I will lay down my life for you.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“Will you really lay down your life for me? Very truly I tell you, before the rooster crows, you will disown me three times!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26669AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26669AY\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><span class=\"woj\">“Do not let your hearts be troubled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26670A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26670A\"></sup> You believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26670B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26670B\"></sup> in God;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26670C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26670C\"></sup> believe also in me.</span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>My Father’s house has many rooms; if that were not so, would I have told you that I am going there<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26671D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26671D\"></sup> to prepare a place for you?</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come back<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26672E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26672E\"></sup> and take you to be with me that you also may be where I am.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26672F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26672F\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You know the way to the place where I am going.”</span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Thomas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26674G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26674G\"></sup> said to him, “Lord, we don’t know where you are going, so how can we know the way?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26675H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26675H\"></sup> the way<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26675I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26675I\"></sup> and the truth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26675J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26675J\"></sup> and the life.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26675K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26675K\"></sup> No one comes to the Father except through me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26675L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26675L\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If you really know me, you will know my Father as well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26676M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26676M\"></sup> From now on, you do know him and have seen him.”</span>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Philip<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26677N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26677N\"></sup> said, “Lord, show us the Father and that will be enough for us.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jesus answered: <span class=\"woj\">“Don’t you know me, Philip, even after I have been among you such a long time? Anyone who has seen me has seen the Father.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26678O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26678O\"></sup> How can you say, ‘Show us the Father’?</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Don’t you believe that I am in the Father, and that the Father is in me?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26679P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26679P\"></sup> The words I say to you I do not speak on my own authority.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26679Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26679Q\"></sup> Rather, it is the Father, living in me, who is doing his work.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Believe me when I say that I am in the Father and the Father is in me; or at least believe on the evidence of the works themselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26680R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26680R\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Very truly I tell you, whoever believes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26681S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26681S\"></sup> in me will do the works I have been doing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26681T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26681T\"></sup> and they will do even greater things than these, because I am going to the Father.</span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And I will do whatever you ask<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26682U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26682U\"></sup> in my name, so that the Father may be glorified in the Son.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You may ask me for anything in my name, and I will do it.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“If you love me, keep my commands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26684V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26684V\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another advocate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26685W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26685W\"></sup> to help you and be with you forever—</span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the Spirit of truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26686X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26686X\"></sup> The world cannot accept him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26686Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26686Y\"></sup> because it neither sees him nor knows him. But you know him, for he lives with you and will be in you.</span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I will not leave you as orphans;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26687Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26687Z\"></sup> I will come to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26687AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26687AA\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Before long, the world will not see me anymore, but you will see me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26688AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26688AB\"></sup> Because I live, you also will live.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26688AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26688AC\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>On that day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26689AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26689AD\"></sup> you will realize that I am in my Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26689AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26689AE\"></sup> and you are in me, and I am in you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26689AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26689AF\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Whoever has my commands and keeps them is the one who loves me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26690AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26690AG\"></sup> The one who loves me will be loved by my Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26690AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26690AH\"></sup> and I too will love them and show myself to them.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Judas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26691AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26691AI\"></sup> (not Judas Iscariot) said, “But, Lord, why do you intend to show yourself to us and not to the world?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26691AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26691AJ\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“Anyone who loves me will obey my teaching.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26692AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26692AK\"></sup> My Father will love them, and we will come to them and make our home with them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26692AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26692AL\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Anyone who does not love me will not obey my teaching. These words you hear are not my own; they belong to the Father who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26693AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26693AM\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“All this I have spoken while still with you.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But the Advocate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26695AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26695AN\"></sup> the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26695AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26695AO\"></sup> will teach you all things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26695AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26695AP\"></sup> and will remind you of everything I have said to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26695AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26695AQ\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Peace I leave with you; my peace I give you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26696AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26696AR\"></sup> I do not give to you as the world gives. Do not let your hearts be troubled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26696AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26696AS\"></sup> and do not be afraid.</span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“You heard me say, ‘I am going away and I am coming back to you.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26697AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26697AT\"></sup> If you loved me, you would be glad that I am going to the Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26697AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26697AU\"></sup> for the Father is greater than I.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26697AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26697AV\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I have told you now before it happens, so that when it does happen you will believe.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26698AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26698AW\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I will not say much more to you, for the prince of this world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26699AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26699AX\"></sup> is coming. He has no hold over me,</span>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>but he comes so that the world may learn that I love the Father and do exactly what my Father has commanded me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26700AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26700AY\"></sup></span><span class=\"woj\">“Come now; let us leave.</span>"
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><span class=\"woj\">“I am<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26701A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26701A\"></sup> the true vine,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26701B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26701B\"></sup> and my Father is the gardener.</span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He cuts off every branch in me that bears no fruit,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26702C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26702C\"></sup> while every branch that does bear fruit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26702D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26702D\"></sup> he prunes so that it will be even more fruitful.</span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You are already clean because of the word I have spoken to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26703E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26703E\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Remain in me, as I also remain in you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26704F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26704F\"></sup> No branch can bear fruit by itself; it must remain in the vine. Neither can you bear fruit unless you remain in me.</span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“I am the vine; you are the branches. If you remain in me and I in you, you will bear much fruit;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26705G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26705G\"></sup> apart from me you can do nothing.</span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>If you do not remain in me, you are like a branch that is thrown away and withers; such branches are picked up, thrown into the fire and burned.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26706H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26706H\"></sup></span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>If you remain in me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26707I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26707I\"></sup> and my words remain in you, ask whatever you wish, and it will be done for you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26707J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26707J\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>This is to my Father’s glory,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26708K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26708K\"></sup> that you bear much fruit, showing yourselves to be my disciples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26708L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26708L\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“As the Father has loved me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26709M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26709M\"></sup> so have I loved you. Now remain in my love.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If you keep my commands,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26710N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26710N\"></sup> you will remain in my love, just as I have kept my Father’s commands and remain in his love.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I have told you this so that my joy may be in you and that your joy may be complete.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26711O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26711O\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>My command is this: Love each other as I have loved you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26712P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26712P\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Greater love has no one than this: to lay down one’s life for one’s friends.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26713Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26713Q\"></sup></span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You are my friends<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26714R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26714R\"></sup> if you do what I command.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26714S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26714S\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I no longer call you servants, because a servant does not know his master’s business. Instead, I have called you friends, for everything that I learned from my Father I have made known to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26715T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26715T\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You did not choose me, but I chose you and appointed you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26716U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26716U\"></sup> so that you might go and bear fruit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26716V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26716V\"></sup>—fruit that will last—and so that whatever you ask in my name the Father will give you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26716W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26716W\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>This is my command: Love each other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26717X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26717X\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“If the world hates you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26718Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26718Y\"></sup> keep in mind that it hated me first.</span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>If you belonged to the world, it would love you as its own. As it is, you do not belong to the world, but I have chosen you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26719Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26719Z\"></sup> out of the world. That is why the world hates you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26719AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26719AA\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Remember what I told you: ‘A servant is not greater than his master.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26720AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26720AB\"></sup> If they persecuted me, they will persecute you also.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26720AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26720AC\"></sup> If they obeyed my teaching, they will obey yours also.</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They will treat you this way because of my name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26721AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26721AD\"></sup> for they do not know the one who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26721AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26721AE\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>If I had not come and spoken to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26722AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26722AF\"></sup> they would not be guilty of sin; but now they have no excuse for their sin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26722AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26722AG\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whoever hates me hates my Father as well.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>If I had not done among them the works no one else did,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26724AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26724AH\"></sup> they would not be guilty of sin.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26724AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26724AI\"></sup> As it is, they have seen, and yet they have hated both me and my Father.</span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But this is to fulfill what is written in their Law:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26725AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26725AJ\"></sup> ‘They hated me without reason.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26725AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26725AK\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“When the Advocate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26726AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26726AL\"></sup> comes, whom I will send to you from the Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26726AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26726AM\"></sup>—the Spirit of truth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26726AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26726AN\"></sup> who goes out from the Father—he will testify about me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26726AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26726AO\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And you also must testify,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26727AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26727AP\"></sup> for you have been with me from the beginning.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26727AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26727AQ\"></sup></span>"
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span><span class=\"woj\">“All this<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26728A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26728A\"></sup> I have told you so that you will not fall away.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26728B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26728B\"></sup></span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They will put you out of the synagogue;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26729C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26729C\"></sup> in fact, the time is coming when anyone who kills you will think they are offering a service to God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26729D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26729D\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They will do such things because they have not known the Father or me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26730E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26730E\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I have told you this, so that when their time comes you will remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26731F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26731F\"></sup> that I warned you about them. I did not tell you this from the beginning because I was with you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26731G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26731G\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>but now I am going to him who sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26732H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26732H\"></sup> None of you asks me, ‘Where are you going?’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26732I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26732I\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Rather, you are filled with grief<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26733J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26733J\"></sup> because I have said these things.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But very truly I tell you, it is for your good that I am going away. Unless I go away, the Advocate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26734K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26734K\"></sup> will not come to you; but if I go, I will send him to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26734L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26734L\"></sup></span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When he comes, he will prove the world to be in the wrong about sin and righteousness and judgment:</span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>about sin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26736M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26736M\"></sup> because people do not believe in me;</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>about righteousness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26737N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26737N\"></sup> because I am going to the Father,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26737O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26737O\"></sup> where you can see me no longer;</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and about judgment, because the prince of this world<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26738P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26738P\"></sup> now stands condemned.</span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“I have much more to say to you, more than you can now bear.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26739Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26739Q\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But when he, the Spirit of truth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26740R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26740R\"></sup> comes, he will guide you into all the truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26740S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26740S\"></sup> He will not speak on his own; he will speak only what he hears, and he will tell you what is yet to come.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He will glorify me because it is from me that he will receive what he will make known to you.</span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>All that belongs to the Father is mine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26742T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26742T\"></sup> That is why I said the Spirit will receive from me what he will make known to you.”</span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jesus went on to say, <span class=\"woj\">“In a little while<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26743U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26743U\"></sup> you will see me no more, and then after a little while you will see me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26743V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26743V\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>At this, some of his disciples said to one another, “What does he mean by saying, <span class=\"woj\">‘In a little while you will see me no more, and then after a little while you will see me,’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26744W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26744W\"></sup></span> and <span class=\"woj\">‘Because I am going to the Father’</span>?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26744X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26744X\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They kept asking, “What does he mean by <span class=\"woj\">‘a little while’</span>? We don’t understand what he is saying.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jesus saw that they wanted to ask him about this, so he said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Are you asking one another what I meant when I said, ‘In a little while you will see me no more, and then after a little while you will see me’?</span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Very truly I tell you, you will weep and mourn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26747Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26747Y\"></sup> while the world rejoices. You will grieve, but your grief will turn to joy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26747Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26747Z\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>A woman giving birth to a child has pain<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26748AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26748AA\"></sup> because her time has come; but when her baby is born she forgets the anguish because of her joy that a child is born into the world.</span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So with you: Now is your time of grief,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26749AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26749AB\"></sup> but I will see you again<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26749AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26749AC\"></sup> and you will rejoice, and no one will take away your joy.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26749AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26749AD\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In that day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26750AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26750AE\"></sup> you will no longer ask me anything. Very truly I tell you, my Father will give you whatever you ask in my name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26750AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26750AF\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Until now you have not asked for anything in my name. Ask and you will receive,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26751AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26751AG\"></sup> and your joy will be complete.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26751AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26751AH\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Though I have been speaking figuratively,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26752AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26752AI\"></sup> a time is coming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26752AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26752AJ\"></sup> when I will no longer use this kind of language but will tell you plainly about my Father.</span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>In that day you will ask in my name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26753AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26753AK\"></sup> I am not saying that I will ask the Father on your behalf.</span>",
			"27": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>No, the Father himself loves you because you have loved me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26754AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26754AL\"></sup> and have believed that I came from God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26754AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26754AM\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I came from the Father and entered the world; now I am leaving the world and going back to the Father.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26755AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26755AN\"></sup></span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Jesus’ disciples said, “Now you are speaking clearly and without figures of speech.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26756AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26756AO\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now we can see that you know all things and that you do not even need to have anyone ask you questions. This makes us believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26757AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26757AP\"></sup> that you came from God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26757AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26757AQ\"></sup>",
			"31": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“Do you now believe?”</span> Jesus replied.",
			"32": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“A time is coming<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26759AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26759AR\"></sup> and in fact has come when you will be scattered,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26759AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26759AS\"></sup> each to your own home. You will leave me all alone.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26759AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26759AT\"></sup> Yet I am not alone, for my Father is with me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26759AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26759AU\"></sup></span>",
			"33": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“I have told you these things, so that in me you may have peace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26760AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26760AV\"></sup> In this world you will have trouble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26760AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26760AW\"></sup> But take heart! I have overcome<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26760AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26760AX\"></sup> the world.”</span>"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>After Jesus said this, he looked toward heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26761A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26761A\"></sup> and prayed:<span class=\"woj\">“Father, the hour has come.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26761B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26761B\"></sup> Glorify your Son, that your Son may glorify you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26761C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26761C\"></sup></span>",
			"2": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For you granted him authority over all people<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26762D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26762D\"></sup> that he might give eternal life<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26762E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26762E\"></sup> to all those you have given him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26762F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26762F\"></sup></span>",
			"3": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now this is eternal life: that they know you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26763G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26763G\"></sup> the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom you have sent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26763H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26763H\"></sup></span>",
			"4": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I have brought you glory<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26764I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26764I\"></sup> on earth by finishing the work you gave me to do.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26764J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26764J\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And now, Father, glorify me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26765K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26765K\"></sup> in your presence with the glory I had with you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26765L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26765L\"></sup> before the world began.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26765M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26765M\"></sup></span>",
			"6": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“I have revealed you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26766N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26766N\"></sup> to those whom you gave me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26766O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26766O\"></sup> out of the world. They were yours; you gave them to me and they have obeyed your word.</span>",
			"7": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now they know that everything you have given me comes from you.</span>",
			"8": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For I gave them the words you gave me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26768P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26768P\"></sup> and they accepted them. They knew with certainty that I came from you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26768Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26768Q\"></sup> and they believed that you sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26768R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26768R\"></sup></span>",
			"9": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I pray for them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26769S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26769S\"></sup> I am not praying for the world, but for those you have given me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26769T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26769T\"></sup> for they are yours.</span>",
			"10": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>All I have is yours, and all you have is mine.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26770U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26770U\"></sup> And glory has come to me through them.</span>",
			"11": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I will remain in the world no longer, but they are still in the world,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26771V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26771V\"></sup> and I am coming to you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26771W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26771W\"></sup> Holy Father, protect them by the power of your name, the name you gave me, so that they may be one<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26771X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26771X\"></sup> as we are one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26771Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26771Y\"></sup></span>",
			"12": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>While I was with them, I protected them and kept them safe by that name you gave me. None has been lost<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26772Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26772Z\"></sup> except the one doomed to destruction<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26772AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26772AA\"></sup> so that Scripture would be fulfilled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26772AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26772AB\"></sup></span>",
			"13": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“I am coming to you now,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26773AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26773AC\"></sup> but I say these things while I am still in the world, so that they may have the full measure of my joy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26773AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26773AD\"></sup> within them.</span>",
			"14": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have given them your word and the world has hated them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26774AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26774AE\"></sup> for they are not of the world any more than I am of the world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26774AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26774AF\"></sup></span>",
			"15": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>My prayer is not that you take them out of the world but that you protect them from the evil one.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26775AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26775AG\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They are not of the world, even as I am not of it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26776AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26776AH\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Sanctify them by the truth; your word is truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26777AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26777AI\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As you sent me into the world,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26778AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26778AJ\"></sup> I have sent them into the world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26778AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26778AK\"></sup></span>",
			"19": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>For them I sanctify myself, that they too may be truly sanctified.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26779AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26779AL\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“My prayer is not for them alone. I pray also for those who will believe in me through their message,</span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>that all of them may be one,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26781AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26781AM\"></sup> Father, just as you are in me and I am in you.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26781AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26781AN\"></sup> May they also be in us so that the world may believe that you have sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26781AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26781AO\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I have given them the glory that you gave me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26782AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26782AP\"></sup> that they may be one as we are one<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26782AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26782AQ\"></sup>—</span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I in them and you in me—so that they may be brought to complete unity. Then the world will know that you sent me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26783AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26783AR\"></sup> and have loved them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26783AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26783AS\"></sup> even as you have loved me.</span>",
			"24": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Father, I want those you have given me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26784AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26784AT\"></sup> to be with me where I am,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26784AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26784AU\"></sup> and to see my glory,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26784AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26784AV\"></sup> the glory you have given me because you loved me before the creation of the world.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26784AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26784AW\"></sup></span>",
			"25": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“Righteous Father, though the world does not know you,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26785AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26785AX\"></sup> I know you, and they know that you have sent me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26785AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26785AY\"></sup></span>",
			"26": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I have made you known to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26786AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26786AZ\"></sup> and will continue to make you known in order that the love you have for me may be in them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26786BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26786BA\"></sup> and that I myself may be in them.”</span>"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>When he had finished praying, Jesus left with his disciples and crossed the Kidron Valley.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26787B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26787B\"></sup> On the other side there was a garden,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26787C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26787C\"></sup> and he and his disciples went into it.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26787D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26787D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now Judas, who betrayed him, knew the place, because Jesus had often met there with his disciples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26788E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26788E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Judas came to the garden, guiding<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26789F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26789F\"></sup> a detachment of soldiers and some officials from the chief priests and the Pharisees.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26789G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26789G\"></sup> They were carrying torches, lanterns and weapons.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Jesus, knowing all that was going to happen to him,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26790H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26790H\"></sup> went out and asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“Who is it you want?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26790I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26790I\"></sup></span>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Jesus of Nazareth,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26791J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26791J\"></sup> they replied.<span class=\"woj\">“I am he,”</span> Jesus said. (And Judas the traitor was standing there with them.)",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“I am he,”</span> they drew back and fell to the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Again he asked them, <span class=\"woj\">“Who is it you want?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26793K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26793K\"></sup></span>“Jesus of Nazareth,” they said.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“I told you that I am he. If you are looking for me, then let these men go.”</span>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This happened so that the words he had spoken would be fulfilled: <span class=\"woj\">“I have not lost one of those you gave me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26795L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26795L\"></sup></span>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, drew it and struck the high priest’s servant, cutting off his right ear. (The servant’s name was Malchus.)",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jesus commanded Peter, <span class=\"woj\">“Put your sword away! Shall I not drink the cup<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26797M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26797M\"></sup> the Father has given me?”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the detachment of soldiers with its commander and the Jewish officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26798N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26798N\"></sup> arrested Jesus. They bound him",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and brought him first to Annas, who was the father-in-law of Caiaphas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26799O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26799O\"></sup> the high priest that year.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Caiaphas was the one who had advised the Jewish leaders that it would be good if one man died for the people.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26800P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26800P\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Simon Peter and another disciple were following Jesus. Because this disciple was known to the high priest,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26801R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26801R\"></sup> he went with Jesus into the high priest’s courtyard,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26801S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26801S\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>but Peter had to wait outside at the door. The other disciple, who was known to the high priest, came back, spoke to the servant girl on duty there and brought Peter in.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“You aren’t one of this man’s disciples too, are you?” she asked Peter.He replied, “I am not.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26803T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26803T\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It was cold, and the servants and officials stood around a fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26804U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26804U\"></sup> they had made to keep warm. Peter also was standing with them, warming himself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26804V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26804V\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Meanwhile, the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and his teaching.",
			"20": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“I have spoken openly to the world,”</span> Jesus replied. <span class=\"woj\">“I always taught in synagogues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26806X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26806X\"></sup> or at the temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26806Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26806Y\"></sup> where all the Jews come together. I said nothing in secret.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26806Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26806Z\"></sup></span>",
			"21": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Why question me? Ask those who heard me. Surely they know what I said.”</span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When Jesus said this, one of the officials<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26808AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26808AA\"></sup> nearby slapped him in the face.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26808AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26808AB\"></sup> “Is this the way you answer the high priest?” he demanded.",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“If I said something wrong,”</span> Jesus replied, <span class=\"woj\">“testify as to what is wrong. But if I spoke the truth, why did you strike me?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26809AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26809AC\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Annas sent him bound to Caiaphas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26810AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26810AD\"></sup> the high priest.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Meanwhile, Simon Peter was still standing there warming himself.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26811AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26811AF\"></sup> So they asked him, “You aren’t one of his disciples too, are you?”He denied it, saying, “I am not.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26811AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26811AG\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>One of the high priest’s servants, a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26812AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26812AH\"></sup> challenged him, “Didn’t I see you with him in the garden?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26812AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26812AI\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Again Peter denied it, and at that moment a rooster began to crow.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26813AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26813AJ\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the Jewish leaders took Jesus from Caiaphas to the palace of the Roman governor.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26814AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26814AL\"></sup> By now it was early morning, and to avoid ceremonial uncleanness they did not enter the palace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26814AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26814AM\"></sup> because they wanted to be able to eat the Passover.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26814AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26814AN\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So Pilate came out to them and asked, “What charges are you bringing against this man?”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“If he were not a criminal,” they replied, “we would not have handed him over to you.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Pilate said, “Take him yourselves and judge him by your own law.”“But we have no right to execute anyone,” they objected.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>This took place to fulfill what Jesus had said about the kind of death he was going to die.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26818AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26818AO\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Pilate then went back inside the palace,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26819AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26819AP\"></sup> summoned Jesus and asked him, “Are you the king of the Jews?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26819AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26819AQ\"></sup>",
			"34": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Is that your own idea,”</span> Jesus asked, <span class=\"woj\">“or did others talk to you about me?”</span>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“Am I a Jew?” Pilate replied. “Your own people and chief priests handed you over to me. What is it you have done?”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“My kingdom<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26822AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26822AR\"></sup> is not of this world. If it were, my servants would fight to prevent my arrest by the Jewish leaders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26822AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26822AS\"></sup> But now my kingdom is from another place.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26822AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26822AT\"></sup></span>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“You are a king, then!” said Pilate.Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“You say that I am a king. In fact, the reason I was born and came into the world is to testify to the truth.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26823AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26823AU\"></sup> Everyone on the side of truth listens to me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26823AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26823AV\"></sup></span>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“What is truth?” retorted Pilate. With this he went out again to the Jews gathered there and said, “I find no basis for a charge against him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26824AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26824AW\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>But it is your custom for me to release to you one prisoner at the time of the Passover. Do you want me to release ‘the king of the Jews’?”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>They shouted back, “No, not him! Give us Barabbas!” Now Barabbas had taken part in an uprising.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26826AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26826AX\"></sup>"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Then Pilate took Jesus and had him flogged.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26827B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26827B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The soldiers twisted together a crown of thorns and put it on his head. They clothed him in a purple robe",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and went up to him again and again, saying, “Hail, king of the Jews!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26829C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26829C\"></sup> And they slapped him in the face.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26829D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26829D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Once more Pilate came out and said to the Jews gathered there, “Look, I am bringing him out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26830E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26830E\"></sup> to you to let you know that I find no basis for a charge against him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26830F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26830F\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When Jesus came out wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26831G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26831G\"></sup> Pilate said to them, “Here is the man!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>As soon as the chief priests and their officials saw him, they shouted, “Crucify! Crucify!”But Pilate answered, “You take him and crucify him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26832H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26832H\"></sup> As for me, I find no basis for a charge against him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26832I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26832I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Jewish leaders insisted, “We have a law, and according to that law he must die,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26833J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26833J\"></sup> because he claimed to be the Son of God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26833K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26833K\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Pilate heard this, he was even more afraid,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and he went back inside the palace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26835L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26835L\"></sup> “Where do you come from?” he asked Jesus, but Jesus gave him no answer.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26835M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26835M\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Do you refuse to speak to me?” Pilate said. “Don’t you realize I have power either to free you or to crucify you?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“You would have no power over me if it were not given to you from above.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26837N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26837N\"></sup> Therefore the one who handed me over to you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26837O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26837O\"></sup> is guilty of a greater sin.”</span>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>From then on, Pilate tried to set Jesus free, but the Jewish leaders kept shouting, “If you let this man go, you are no friend of Caesar. Anyone who claims to be a king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26838P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26838P\"></sup> opposes Caesar.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Pilate heard this, he brought Jesus out and sat down on the judge’s seat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26839Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26839Q\"></sup> at a place known as the Stone Pavement (which in Aramaic<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26839R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26839R\"></sup> is Gabbatha).",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>It was the day of Preparation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26840S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26840S\"></sup> of the Passover; it was about noon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26840T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26840T\"></sup>“Here is your king,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26840U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26840U\"></sup> Pilate said to the Jews.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But they shouted, “Take him away! Take him away! Crucify him!”“Shall I crucify your king?” Pilate asked.“We have no king but Caesar,” the chief priests answered.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Finally Pilate handed him over to them to be crucified.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26842V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26842V\"></sup>So the soldiers took charge of Jesus.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Carrying his own cross,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26843X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26843X\"></sup> he went out to the place of the Skull<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26843Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26843Y\"></sup> (which in Aramaic<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26843Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26843Z\"></sup> is called Golgotha).",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>There they crucified him, and with him two others<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26844AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26844AA\"></sup>—one on each side and Jesus in the middle.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Pilate had a notice prepared and fastened to the cross. It read: <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">jesus of nazareth</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26845AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26845AB\"></sup> <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">the king of the jews</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26845AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26845AC\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Many of the Jews read this sign, for the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26846AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26846AD\"></sup> and the sign was written in Aramaic, Latin and Greek.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The chief priests of the Jews protested to Pilate, “Do not write ‘The King of the Jews,’ but that this man claimed to be king of the Jews.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26847AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26847AE\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Pilate answered, “What I have written, I have written.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When the soldiers crucified Jesus, they took his clothes, dividing them into four shares, one for each of them, with the undergarment remaining. This garment was seamless, woven in one piece from top to bottom.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Let’s not tear it,” they said to one another. “Let’s decide by lot who will get it.”This happened that the scripture might be fulfilled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26850AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26850AF\"></sup> that said,“They divided my clothes among themand cast lots for my garment.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26850AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26850AG\"></sup>So this is what the soldiers did.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Near the cross<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26851AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26851AH\"></sup> of Jesus stood his mother,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26851AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26851AI\"></sup> his mother’s sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26851AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26851AJ\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Jesus saw his mother<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26852AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26852AK\"></sup> there, and the disciple whom he loved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26852AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26852AL\"></sup> standing nearby, he said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Woman, here is your son,”</span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and to the disciple, <span class=\"woj\">“Here is your mother.”</span> From that time on, this disciple took her into his home.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Later, knowing that everything had now been finished,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26854AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26854AN\"></sup> and so that Scripture would be fulfilled,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26854AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26854AO\"></sup> Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“I am thirsty.”</span>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>A jar of wine vinegar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26855AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26855AP\"></sup> was there, so they soaked a sponge in it, put the sponge on a stalk of the hyssop plant, and lifted it to Jesus’ lips.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When he had received the drink, Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“It is finished.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26856AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26856AQ\"></sup></span> With that, he bowed his head and gave up his spirit.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now it was the day of Preparation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26857AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26857AR\"></sup> and the next day was to be a special Sabbath. Because the Jewish leaders did not want the bodies left on the crosses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26857AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26857AS\"></sup> during the Sabbath, they asked Pilate to have the legs broken and the bodies taken down.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The soldiers therefore came and broke the legs of the first man who had been crucified with Jesus, and then those of the other.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26858AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26858AT\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But when they came to Jesus and found that he was already dead, they did not break his legs.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Instead, one of the soldiers pierced<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26860AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26860AU\"></sup> Jesus’ side with a spear, bringing a sudden flow of blood and water.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26860AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26860AV\"></sup>",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The man who saw it<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26861AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26861AW\"></sup> has given testimony, and his testimony is true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26861AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26861AX\"></sup> He knows that he tells the truth, and he testifies so that you also may believe.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>These things happened so that the scripture would be fulfilled:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26862AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26862AY\"></sup> “Not one of his bones will be broken,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26862AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26862AZ\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>and, as another scripture says, “They will look on the one they have pierced.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26863BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26863BA\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Later, Joseph of Arimathea asked Pilate for the body of Jesus. Now Joseph was a disciple of Jesus, but secretly because he feared the Jewish leaders.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26864BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26864BC\"></sup> With Pilate’s permission, he came and took the body away.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>He was accompanied by Nicodemus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26865BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26865BD\"></sup> the man who earlier had visited Jesus at night. Nicodemus brought a mixture of myrrh and aloes, about seventy-five pounds.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Taking Jesus’ body, the two of them wrapped it, with the spices, in strips of linen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26866BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26866BE\"></sup> This was in accordance with Jewish burial customs.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26866BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26866BF\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>At the place where Jesus was crucified, there was a garden, and in the garden a new tomb, in which no one had ever been laid.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Because it was the Jewish day of Preparation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26868BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26868BG\"></sup> and since the tomb was nearby,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26868BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26868BH\"></sup> they laid Jesus there."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Early on the first day of the week, while it was still dark, Mary Magdalene<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26869B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26869B\"></sup> went to the tomb and saw that the stone had been removed from the entrance.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26869C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26869C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So she came running to Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one Jesus loved,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26870D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26870D\"></sup> and said, “They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we don’t know where they have put him!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26870E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26870E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Peter and the other disciple started for the tomb.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26871F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26871F\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Both were running, but the other disciple outran Peter and reached the tomb first.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He bent over and looked in<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26873G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26873G\"></sup> at the strips of linen<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26873H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26873H\"></sup> lying there but did not go in.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Simon Peter came along behind him and went straight into the tomb. He saw the strips of linen lying there,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>as well as the cloth that had been wrapped around Jesus’ head.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26875I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26875I\"></sup> The cloth was still lying in its place, separate from the linen.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Finally the other disciple, who had reached the tomb first,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26876J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26876J\"></sup> also went inside. He saw and believed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>(They still did not understand from Scripture<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26877K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26877K\"></sup> that Jesus had to rise from the dead.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26877L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26877L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then the disciples went back to where they were staying.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Mary stood outside the tomb crying. As she wept, she bent over to look into the tomb<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26879M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26879M\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and saw two angels in white,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26880N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26880N\"></sup> seated where Jesus’ body had been, one at the head and the other at the foot.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They asked her, “Woman, why are you crying?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26881O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26881O\"></sup>“They have taken my Lord away,” she said, “and I don’t know where they have put him.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26881P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26881P\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>At this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing there,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26882Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26882Q\"></sup> but she did not realize that it was Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26882R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26882R\"></sup>",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He asked her, <span class=\"woj\">“Woman, why are you crying?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26883S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26883S\"></sup> Who is it you are looking for?”</span>Thinking he was the gardener, she said, “Sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have put him, and I will get him.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Jesus said to her, <span class=\"woj\">“Mary.”</span>She turned toward him and cried out in Aramaic,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26884T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26884T\"></sup> “Rabboni!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26884U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26884U\"></sup> (which means “Teacher”).",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Do not hold on to me, for I have not yet ascended to the Father. Go instead to my brothers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26885V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26885V\"></sup> and tell them, ‘I am ascending to my Father<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26885W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26885W\"></sup> and your Father, to my God and your God.’”</span>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Mary Magdalene<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26886X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26886X\"></sup> went to the disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26886Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26886Y\"></sup> with the news: “I have seen the Lord!” And she told them that he had said these things to her.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>On the evening of that first day of the week, when the disciples were together, with the doors locked for fear of the Jewish leaders,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26887Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26887Z\"></sup> Jesus came and stood among them and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26887AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26887AA\"></sup> be with you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26887AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26887AB\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After he said this, he showed them his hands and side.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26888AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26888AC\"></sup> The disciples were overjoyed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26888AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26888AD\"></sup> when they saw the Lord.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Again Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Peace be with you!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26889AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26889AE\"></sup> As the Father has sent me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26889AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26889AF\"></sup> I am sending you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26889AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26889AG\"></sup></span>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And with that he breathed on them and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Receive the Holy Spirit.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26890AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26890AH\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>If you forgive anyone’s sins, their sins are forgiven; if you do not forgive them, they are not forgiven.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26891AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26891AI\"></sup></span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now Thomas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26892AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26892AJ\"></sup> (also known as Didymus), one of the Twelve, was not with the disciples when Jesus came.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So the other disciples told him, “We have seen the Lord!”But he said to them, “Unless I see the nail marks in his hands and put my finger where the nails were, and put my hand into his side,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26893AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26893AK\"></sup> I will not believe.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26893AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26893AL\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>A week later his disciples were in the house again, and Thomas was with them. Though the doors were locked, Jesus came and stood among them and said, <span class=\"woj\">“Peace<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26894AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26894AM\"></sup> be with you!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26894AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26894AN\"></sup></span>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then he said to Thomas, <span class=\"woj\">“Put your finger here; see my hands. Reach out your hand and put it into my side. Stop doubting and believe.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26895AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26895AO\"></sup></span>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Thomas said to him, “My Lord and my God!”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Jesus told him, <span class=\"woj\">“Because you have seen me, you have believed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26897AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26897AP\"></sup> blessed are those who have not seen and yet have believed.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26897AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26897AQ\"></sup></span>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Jesus performed many other signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26898AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26898AR\"></sup> in the presence of his disciples, which are not recorded in this book.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26898AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26898AS\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But these are written that you may believe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26899AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26899AT\"></sup> that Jesus is the Messiah, the Son of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26899AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26899AU\"></sup> and that by believing you may have life in his name.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26899AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26899AV\"></sup>"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Afterward Jesus appeared again to his disciples,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26900A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26900A\"></sup> by the Sea of Galilee.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26900B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26900B\"></sup> It happened this way:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Simon Peter, Thomas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26901C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26901C\"></sup> (also known as Didymus), Nathanael<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26901D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26901D\"></sup> from Cana in Galilee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26901E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26901E\"></sup> the sons of Zebedee,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26901F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26901F\"></sup> and two other disciples were together.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“I’m going out to fish,” Simon Peter told them, and they said, “We’ll go with you.” So they went out and got into the boat, but that night they caught nothing.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26902G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26902G\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Early in the morning, Jesus stood on the shore, but the disciples did not realize that it was Jesus.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26903H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26903H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He called out to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Friends, haven’t you any fish?”</span>“No,” they answered.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said, <span class=\"woj\">“Throw your net on the right side of the boat and you will find some.”</span> When they did, they were unable to haul the net in because of the large number of fish.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26905I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26905I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the disciple whom Jesus loved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26906J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26906J\"></sup> said to Peter, “It is the Lord!” As soon as Simon Peter heard him say, “It is the Lord,” he wrapped his outer garment around him (for he had taken it off) and jumped into the water.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The other disciples followed in the boat, towing the net full of fish, for they were not far from shore, about a hundred yards.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When they landed, they saw a fire<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26908K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26908K\"></sup> of burning coals there with fish on it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26908L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26908L\"></sup> and some bread.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Bring some of the fish you have just caught.”</span>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Simon Peter climbed back into the boat and dragged the net ashore. It was full of large fish, 153, but even with so many the net was not torn.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Jesus said to them, <span class=\"woj\">“Come and have breakfast.”</span> None of the disciples dared ask him, “Who are you?” They knew it was the Lord.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Jesus came, took the bread and gave it to them, and did the same with the fish.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26912M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26912M\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>This was now the third time Jesus appeared to his disciples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26913N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26913N\"></sup> after he was raised from the dead.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When they had finished eating, Jesus said to Simon Peter, <span class=\"woj\">“Simon son of John, do you love me more than these?”</span>“Yes, Lord,” he said, “you know that I love you.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26914O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26914O\"></sup>Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Feed my lambs.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26914P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26914P\"></sup></span>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Again Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Simon son of John, do you love me?”</span>He answered, “Yes, Lord, you know that I love you.”Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Take care of my sheep.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26915Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26915Q\"></sup></span>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The third time he said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Simon son of John, do you love me?”</span>Peter was hurt because Jesus asked him the third time, <span class=\"woj\">“Do you love me?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26916R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26916R\"></sup></span> He said, “Lord, you know all things;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26916S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26916S\"></sup> you know that I love you.”Jesus said, <span class=\"woj\">“Feed my sheep.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26916T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26916T\"></sup></span>",
			"18": "<span class=\"woj\"><sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Very truly I tell you, when you were younger you dressed yourself and went where you wanted; but when you are old you will stretch out your hands, and someone else will dress you and lead you where you do not want to go.”</span>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Jesus said this to indicate the kind of death<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26918U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26918U\"></sup> by which Peter would glorify God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26918V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26918V\"></sup> Then he said to him, <span class=\"woj\">“Follow me!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26918W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26918W\"></sup></span>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Peter turned and saw that the disciple whom Jesus loved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26919X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26919X\"></sup> was following them. (This was the one who had leaned back against Jesus at the supper and had said, “Lord, who is going to betray you?”)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26919Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26919Y\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When Peter saw him, he asked, “Lord, what about him?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Jesus answered, <span class=\"woj\">“If I want him to remain alive until I return,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26921Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26921Z\"></sup> what is that to you? You must follow me.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26921AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26921AA\"></sup></span>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Because of this, the rumor spread among the believers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26922AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26922AB\"></sup> that this disciple would not die. But Jesus did not say that he would not die; he only said, <span class=\"woj\">“If I want him to remain alive until I return, what is that to you?”</span>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>This is the disciple who testifies to these things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26923AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26923AC\"></sup> and who wrote them down. We know that his testimony is true.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26923AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26923AD\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Jesus did many other things as well.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-26924AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-26924AE\"></sup> If every one of them were written down, I suppose that even the whole world would not have room for the books that would be written."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;